COPY public.mail_templates (id, hashtag, lang, subject, description, contents) FROM stdin;
1	#NewMembreshipRecommender	default	{{appName}}: Welcome as a recommender	Mail to user to acknowledge their status of recommender	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>You are now a recommender of {{appName}}. We thank you for your time and support.</p>\r\n<p>The role of a recommender is very similar to that of a journal editor (finding reviewers, collecting reviews, making editorial decisions based on reviews), with the possibility of recommending the preprints you have chosen to handle after one or after several rounds of reviews. The evaluation process is designed to guide decisions as to whether to ‘Revise’, ‘Recommend’ or ‘Reject’ the preprint.</p>\r\n<p>A preprint recommended by {{appName}} is an article that may be used and cited like any ‘classic’ article published in a peer-reviewed journal. If you decide to recommend a preprint, you will need to write a “recommendation”, which will have its own DOI and be published by {{appName}} under the license CC-BY-ND. The recommendation is a short article, similar to a News &amp; Views piece. It has its own title, contains between about 300 and 1500 words, describes the context and explains why the preprint is particularly interesting. The limitations of the preprint can also be discussed. This text also contains references (citing, at least, the preprint being recommended). All the editorial correspondence (reviews, your decisions, authors’ replies) will also be published by {{appName}}.</p>\r\n<p>As a recommender for {{appName}},</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>You can recommend up to five articles per year. Details about the recommendation process can be found here <a href="{{helpurl}}">{{helpurl}}</a> and in this short <a href="https://youtu.be/u5greO-q8-M">video</a>.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>You will be expected to comply with the code of conduct of {{appName}}, which can be found here: <a href="{{ethicsurl}}">{{ethicsurl}}</a></li>\r\n<li>You are eligible for selection as a member of the Managing Board for a period of two years.</li>\r\n<li>You will be notified about new articles recommended by {{appName}}, according to your requested notification frequency and fields of interest.</li>\r\n<li>You will also receive requests to initiate preprint evaluations in your fields of interest with a view to recommending them.</li>\r\n<li>You can propose the nomination of new recommenders to the Managing Board.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>There is also a guide for PCI recommenders <a href="https://peercommunityin.org/2020/10/28/pci-recommender-guide/">here</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Thanks again for your interest, your help and your support.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
2	#AdminNewUser	default	{{appName}}: A new user has signed up	Mail to MB to indicate the registration of new user	<p>Dear administrators,</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">A new user has joined {{appName}}: {{userTxt}} ({{userMail}}).</p>\r\n<p>If this user can act as a recommender, you should change their status.</p>\r\n<p>Have a nice day!</p>
3	#NewsLetterWeekly	default	{{appName}}: Newsletter	Mail to users that choose to receive the newsletter every week	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>See below for the latest updates from {{appName}}.</p>\r\n<p>Best regards,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
4	#CoRecommenderAddedOnArticleAlreadyPublished	default	{{appName}}: Your co-recommendation of a {{articlePrePost}}	Mail to co-recommender to inform them that they have been declared as a co-recommender of a postprint	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>A recommendation text for the {{articlePrePost}} by {{articleAuthors}} and entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> (<a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>) is under consideration. You have been declared as a co-recommender of this {{articlePrePost}}. You can view the recommendation by following this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or by logging onto the {{appName}} website and going to 'For recommenders —&gt; Your recommendations of posprints' in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p>We are currently handling this recommendation; it will probably be rapidly posted on the {{appName}} website.</p>\r\n<p>If you do not wish to co-author this recommendation, please contact us as soon as possible. Otherwise, we thank you for co-writing this recommendation.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
5	#CoRecommenderAddedOnArticle	default	{{appName}}: Your co-recommendation of a {{articlePrePost}}	Mail to co-recommender to inform them that they have been declared as a co-recommender of a preprint	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>A peer-review evaluation of a preprint by {{articleAuthors}} and entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> (<a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>) is currenlty handled by the recommender {{recommenderPerson}}. This recommender declared you as a co-recommender and, as such, as a co-author of the recommendation if they decide to recommend this preprint. The reviews and the recommendation text can be viewed by clicking on this link: <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or by logging onto the {{appName}} website and going to 'For recommenders —&gt; Preprint you are co-handling' in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p>We remind you that a preprint is recommended if, and only if it is scientifically valid and of high quality and the code of conduct has been followed. The decision to recommend a preprint must be based on high-quality reviews. We also remind you that the recommendation text, all the editorial correspondence (reviews, decisions, your recommendation and authors’ replies) will be published by {{appName}}. Being a co-recommender for this preprint means that you share full responsibility with the recommender for the public recommendation of this preprint.</p>\r\n<p>If you do not wish to be a co-recommender of this preprint, please contact us as soon as possible. Otherwise, we thank you for this contribution to {{appName}}.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
6	#CoRecommenderRemovedFromArticle	default	{{appName}}: Your co-recommendation of a {{articlePrePost}}	Mail to co-recommender to inform them that they have been removed as a co-recommender of a preprint	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>A recommendation text for the {{articlePrePost}} by {{articleAuthors}} and entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> (<a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>) is under consideration.</p>\r\n<p>You have been removed as co-recommender of this {{articlePrePost}}.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
7	#CoRecommendersArticleRecommended	default	{{appName}}: Your co-recommendation of a {{articlePrePost}}	Mail to co-recommenders to let them know that the preprint is now recommended	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>The recommendation for the {{articlePrePost}} by {{articleAuthors}} and entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> (<a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>) is now published on {{appName}} website.</p>\r\n<p>You can find it there: <a href="{{recommDOI}}">{{recommDOI}}</a></p>\r\n<p>And there: <a href="{{linkRecomm}}">{{linkRecomm}}</a></p>\r\n<p>Do not hesitate to share the news as much as possible: social networks if you are on them, mailing, websites, CV, quotation, etc...</p>\r\n<p>We thank you for co-writing this recommendation.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
8	#CoRecommendersArticleStatusChanged	default	{{appName}}: Your co-recommendation of a {{articlePrePost}}	Mail to co-recommenders to indicate the change of the status of the preprint	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>You are co-recommender of the article by {{articleAuthors}} entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> (<a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>).</p>\r\n<p>The status of this article has changed from "{{tOldStatus}}" to "{{tNewStatus}}".</p>\r\n<p>You can view the evaluation process by following this link: <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or by logging onto the {{appName}} website and going to 'For recommenders —&gt; Your recommendation of posprints (if it is a posprint) or —&gt; Preprints you are co-handling (if it is a preprint)' in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
9	#ManagersArticleCancelled	default	{{appName}}: Article cancelled	Mail to MB to indicate that the submitter cancelled their submission	<p>Dear members of the Managing Board,</p>\r\n<p>The submission of the article entitled "{{articleTitle}}" has been cancelled by the author.</p>\r\n<p>To manage this recommendation, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Have a nice day!</p>
10	#ManagersArticleConsideredForRecommendation	default	{{appName}}: Article considered for recommendation	Mail to MB to indicate that a recommender took a preprint in charge	<p>Dear members of the Managing Board,</p>\r\n<p>{{recommenderPerson}} has agreed to handle the article entitled "<strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong>" submitted to {{appName}}.</p>\r\n<p>To see and manage this evaluation process, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Have a nice day!</p>
12	#ManagersArticleStatusChanged	default	{{appName}}: Article status changed	Mail to MB to indicate the change of a status of the preprint 	<p>Dear members of the Managing Board,</p>\r\n<p>The status of the article entitled "{{articleTitle}}" changed from "{{tOldStatus}}" to "{{tNewStatus}}".</p>\r\n<p>To manage this recommendation, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Have a nice day!</p>
13	#ManagersPreprintSubmission	default	{{appName}}: Preprint submission	Mail to MB to indicate the submission of a preprint	<p>Dear members of the Managing Board,</p>\r\n<p>{{appName}} has received a submission of a preprint by {{submitterPerson}} entitled <strong data-mce-fragment="1">{{articleTitle}}</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>To check this submission, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a>.</p>\r\n<div class="p-rich_text_section"><strong>WARNING:</strong> <strong>do not validate it unless you (or someone else in the managing board) have checked the following points:</strong></div>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Files are readable, lines are numbered</li>\r\n<li>DOI of (or permanent link to) the article, data, and script are correct,</li>\r\n<li>Data, scripts/code, and supplementary information are available</li>\r\n<li>A readme file is present with the data and script</li>\r\n<li>Mandatory sections are there ("funding", "Conflict of Interest disclosure", "Data, script, code, and supplementary information availability")</li>\r\n<li>No obvious financial conflicts of interest appear</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div class="p-rich_text_section">Have a nice day!</div>
14	#ManagersRecommendationOrDecision	default	{{appName}}: A decision or recommendation has been posted by a recommender	Mail to MB to indicate that a decision or a recommendation has been posted by a recommender	<p>Dear members of the Managing Board,<br><br>A decision or a recommendation for the article "<strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong>" has been written by {{recommenderPerson}} for {{appName}}. To see this recommendation or decision, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a>.<br><br><strong>WARNING: do not&nbsp;validate this decision directly, unless you (or someone else in the managing board) have checked the following points:</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>In case of a "revise" or "reject" decision, please check that:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Reviews are not too short and look ok</li>\r\n<li>Reviews are not pasted in the decision box (otherwise delete them)</li>\r\n<li>The decision looks fine on the tone and is overall in agreement with the reviews</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>In case of a "recommendation" decision, please check that:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The recommendation has a title</li>\r\n<li>The recommendation clearly explains why the article is recommended</li>\r\n<li>The PCI office gave you the green light to validate the recommendation publication</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Have a nice day!</p>
15	#NewMembreshipManager	default	{{appName}}: Welcome to the Managing Board	Mail to recommender to acknowledge their status of manager	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>You have recently joined the Managing Board of {{appName}}. We thank you warmly for agreeing to join the Board and for your time and support for this community.</p>\r\n<p>The members of the Managing Board of {{appName}} are responsible for accepting/rejecting new recommenders. They also deal with any problems arising between authors and the recommenders who have evaluated/recommended their articles. They detect and deal with dysfunctions of {{appName}}, and may exclude recommenders, if necessary. They also rapidly check the quality of formatting and deontology for the reviews and recommendations published by {{appName}}. Finally, members of the Managing Board of {{appName}} are members of the non-profit organization “Peer Community in”. This non-profit organization is responsible for the creation and functioning of the various thematic PCIs.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
16	#NewUser	default	{{appName}}: Welcome as a new user	Mail to user to acknowledge their registration	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>You have recently joined {{appName}}. Thank you for your interest and for registering with us.</p>\r\n<p>More information about {{appName}} can be found here <a href="{{baseurl}}">{{baseurl}}</a> and in this <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4PZhpnc8wwo">video</a>.</p>\r\n<p>As a user, you can submit your preprints {{appName}} for evaluation and recommendation - and find five good reasons to do so in this short <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jMhVl__gupg">video</a>. Briefly, your preprints must first be deposited on a preprint server, such as bioRxiv, and must not already be under review for publication in a traditional journal.</p>\r\n<p>When submitting your preprints, you are allowed to suggest recommenders. A recommender is very similar to a journal editor (responsible for finding reviewers, collecting reviews, and making editorial decisions based on reviews), and may eventually recommend your preprint after one or several rounds of reviews. A preprint recommended by {{appName}} is an article that may be used and cited like any ‘classic’ article published in a peer-reviewed journal.</p>\r\n<p>Once you have submitted your preprint, one of the recommenders you suggest, or any other recommenders from the community may express an interest in initiating the evaluation process for your preprint, which will involve sending your preprint out for peer review.</p>\r\n<p>If you wish to submit a preprint, please click on the "Submit a preprint" button on the home page of the {{appName}} website.</p>\r\n<p>You can edit your account profile (in the right corner of the tool bar) in order to receive the PCI newsletter concerning published recommendations.</p>\r\n<p>Finally, if you are interested in becoming a recommender for {{appName}} - <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2BDrPoHGkn0">see video</a> - please contact a current recommender in your field via this link <a href="{{recommurl}}">{{recommurl}}</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Thanks again for your interest and for joining {{appName}}.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
17	#NewUserParallelSubmissionAllowed	default	{{appName}}: Welcome as a new user	Mail to user to acknowledge their registration in PCI allowing parallel submission	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>You have recently joined {{appLongName}}. Thank you for your interest and for registering with us.</p>\r\n<p>More information about {{appName}} can be found here <a href="{{baseurl}}">{{baseurl}}</a> and in this <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4PZhpnc8wwo">video</a>.</p>\r\n<p>As a user, you can submit your preprints to {{appName}} for evaluation and recommendation - and find five good reasons to do so in this short <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jMhVl__gupg">video</a>. Briefly, your preprints must first be deposited on a preprint server, such as bioRxiv, and you must choose between A) exclusive submission to {{appName}}, or B) parallel submission with journals. Please go to <a href="{{infourl}}">{{infourl}}</a> for more information on these options.</p>\r\n<p>When submitting your preprints, you are allowed to suggest recommenders. A recommender is very similar to a journal editor (responsible for finding reviewers, collecting reviews, and making editorial decisions based on reviews), and may eventually recommend your preprint after one or several rounds of reviews. A preprint recommended by {{appLongName}} is an article that may be used and cited like any ‘classic’ article published in a peer-reviewed journal.</p>\r\n<p>Once you have submitted your preprint, one of the recommenders you suggest, or any other recommenders from the community may express an interest in initiating the evaluation process for your preprint, which will involve sending your preprint out for peer review.</p>\r\n<p>If you wish to submit a preprint, please click on the "Submit a preprint" button on the home page of the {{appName}} website.</p>\r\n<p>As a user, you will also receive alerts every {{days}} concerning recommendations in the following fields published on the {{appLongName}} web site: {{thematics}}.</p>\r\n<p>Finally, if you are interested in becoming a recommender for {{appName}} - <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2BDrPoHGkn0">see video</a> - please contact a current recommender in your field via this link <a href="{{recommurl}}">{{recommurl}}</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Thanks again for your interest and for joining {{appLongName}}.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appLongName}}</p>
18	#RecommenderArticleStatusChanged	default	{{appName}}: Change in article status	Mail to recommender to indicate the change of the status of the preprint	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>You have initiated the evaluation of the article entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> by {{articleAuthors}} (<a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>).</p>\r\n<p>The status of this article has changed from "{{tOldStatus}}" to "{{tNewStatus}}".</p>\r\n<p>You can view and manage your evaluation process by following this link: <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or by logging onto the {{appName}} website and going to 'For recommenders —&gt; Preprints you are handling' in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p>We thank you for managing this evaluation.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
19	#RecommenderPostprintStatusChanged	default	{{appName}}: Change in article status	Mail to recommender to indicate a change in the status of their recommendation of a postprint	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>You have submitted your recommendation of the postprint article entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> by {{articleAuthors}} (<a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>).</p>\r\n<p>The status of this article has changed from "{{tOldStatus}}" to "{{tNewStatus}}".</p>\r\n<p>You can view and manage your evaluation process by following this link: <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or by logging onto the {{appName}} website and going to 'For recommenders —&gt; Your recommendations of postprints' in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p>We thank you for managing this evaluation.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
20	#RecommenderStatusChangedToUnderConsideration	default	{{appName}}: Revised version	Mail to recommender to indicate that a revised version has been submitted and that they must make a decision	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>A revised version of the preprint entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}},</strong> by {{articleAuthors}}, has been submitted by the authors along with replies to your comments and those of the reviewers. You’ll find these replies, along with a link to the clean version and, if included, a version of the revised manuscript with track changes at this address <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> (also see the links at the end of this message).</p>\r\n<p>For this round of evaluation, you must reach a decision to ‘Revise’, ‘Recommend’ or ‘Reject’ the preprint.</p>\r\n<p>Our advice is <strong>to make your decision directly, if possible, using the previous reviews and the author’s resubmission letter</strong>. In this case, we expect to receive your decision within the next 10 days (and preferably within a week). If you need more time, please let us know by return mail.</p>\r\n<p>If you feel that you need to send the revised version for a second round of peer review, you will need to re-invite the reviewers (please see the <a href=".../help/help_practical">"how to?" section</a> of the website).</p>\r\n<p>If you decide to recommend this preprint, you will need to write a "recommendation" that will have its own DOI and will be published by {{appName}} under the license CC-BY. The recommendation is a short article, similar to a News &amp; Views piece. It has its own title, contains between about 300 and 1500 words, describes the context and explains why the preprint is particularly interesting. The limitations of the preprint can also be discussed. This text also contains references (citing, at least, the preprint being recommended). All the editorial correspondence (reviews, your decisions, authors’ replies) relating to the preprint will also be published by {{appName}}.</p>\r\n<p>We look forward to your decision. Thanks in advance!</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
21	#RecommenderStatusChangedUnderToRecommended	default	{{appName}}: Article recommended	Mail to recommender to indicate them that the preprint is now recommended	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>Your recommendation - along with the reviews - is now posted on the {{appName}} website.</p>\r\n<p>You can find it there: <a href="{{doiRecomm}}">{{doiRecomm}}</a></p>\r\n<p>And there: <a href="{{linkRecomm}}">{{linkRecomm}}</a></p>\r\n<p>You will find the reference to your recommendation and that of the recommended article.</p>\r\n<p>Do not hesitate to share the news as much as possible: social networks if you are on them, mailing, websites, CV, quotation, etc...</p>\r\n<p>Thanks again for recommending this article for {{appName}}.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
22	#RecommenderSuggestedArticle	default	{{appName}}: Request to act as a recommender for a preprint	Mail to suggested recommenders to ask them to act as recommender of a submitted preprint	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>The authors of a preprint entitled&nbsp;<strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> by {{articleAuthors}} (<a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>) have suggested you as a possible recommender for their article.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Very important: </strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>You should agree to become the recommender for this preprint only if, after reading it, you think that it is interesting and merits evaluation</strong> (relevant research question, quality of the methods/data/analysis, etc.).</p>\r\n<p>You can obtain information about this request and accept or decline this invitation by following this link&nbsp;<a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a>&nbsp;or by logging on to the {{appName}} website and going to 'For recommenders —&gt; Request(s) to handle a preprint' in the tool bar.</p>\r\n<p>This article is considered to lie within the scope of the PCI, but there has been no scientific filtering by the managing board. The article may, therefore, be of poor scientific quality and, if this is the case, it would be better to reject it directly, without peer review. So, <strong>if you feel that this preprint is of insufficient quality, please decline this request to handle it.</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Important information before you agree to become the recommender for this preprint:</strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The role of a recommender is very similar to that of a journal editor (finding reviewers, collecting reviews, taking editorial decisions based on reviews). The decision to ‘Revise’, ‘Recommend’ or ‘Reject’ the preprint is based on the recommender’s evaluation. A preprint recommended by {{appName}} is an article that may be used and cited like the ‘classic’ articles published in peer-reviewed journals. Recommended preprints are valid, citable and final articles. The normal outcome is therefore to leave them on preprint servers or open repositories. However, the authors of a PCI-recommended article may prefer:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>To publish their article in the Peer Community journal as is, immediately and at no cost</li>\r\n<li>To submit it to a PCI-friendly journal (acceptance with no further peer review OR response within 5 days OR use of the PCI evaluation if appropriate).</li>\r\n<li>To submit it to another journal.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Details about the recommendation process can be found&nbsp;<a href="https://peercommunityin.org/2020/10/28/pci-recommender-guide/">here</a>.</p>\r\n<p>By agreeing to become the recommender for this preprint, you agree to do your best to handle the peer-review process within as short a time period as possible for the authors. Indeed, this rapid turnaround time is a key factor for the success of PCI as a credible alternative to journals.</p>\r\n<p>To this end, we need you:</p>\r\n<p>1-&nbsp;<strong>To send invitations to 5-10 potential reviewers within 24 hours of agreeing to become the recommender for this preprint</strong><strong> </strong>and to continue sending out new invitations until you find at least two reviewers willing to review the preprint. Sending multiple invitations increases the chances of finding available reviewers and keeping turnaround times short. You may, of course, use whichever strategy you prefer to invite reviewers. The key thing is avoiding situations in which only a couple of invitations have been sent out in 20 days, with only one reply after 30 days.<br>2-&nbsp;<strong>To post your decision,</strong>&nbsp;ideally <strong>within 10 days</strong>&nbsp;of receiving the reviews. <br>3-&nbsp;<strong>To write a recommendation text </strong><strong>(i.e. a text of 300 to 1,500 words describing the context and explaining why</strong> the preprint is particularly interesting)&nbsp;if you decide to recommend this preprint for {{appName}} at the end of the evaluation process, and to submit it as soon as possible after deciding to recommend the article.<br>4-&nbsp;<strong>To declare that you have no conflict of interest with the authors or the content of the article.</strong>&nbsp; See the <a href="https://peercommunityin.org/">code of conduct</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Details about the recommendation process can be found <a href="https://peercommunityin.org/2020/10/28/pci-recommender-guide/">here</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Thank you for your help.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
24	#RecommenderSuggestionNotNeededAnymore	default	{{appName}}: Request cancelled	Mail to suggested recommenders to indicate that another recommender took the preprint in charge	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>For this preprint, your help as a recommender is no longer needed.</p>\r\n<p>You were suggested as a recommender for a preprint entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> by {{articleAuthors}} (DOI <a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>). This preprint attracted the attention of another {{appName}} recommender, who has initiated its evaluation. Consequently, this preprint no longer appears in your list of requests to act as a recommender on the {{appName}} webpage.</p>\r\n<p>If you would still like to participate in the evaluation of this preprint, please send us an e-mail at {{appContactLink}}. We will inform the recommender handling the evaluation process of your willingness to participate and they may then contact you.</p>\r\n<p>We hope that, in the near future, you will have the opportunity to initiate the evaluation of another preprint.</p>\r\n<p>Thank you for your support.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
25	#RecommenderThankForPostprint	default	{{appName}}: Thank you for initiating a recommendation!	Mail to recommender to acknowledge its willingness to recommend a postprint	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>You have decided to recommend a postprint entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong>. To view and/or manage your recommendation, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or logging onto the {{appName}} website and going to 'For recommenders —&gt; Your recommendations of postprints' in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p>We thank you in advance for writing this recommendation.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
26	#RecommenderThankForPreprint	default	{{appName}}: Thank you for handling the evaluation of a preprint 	Mail to recommender to thanks them for taking a preprint in charge	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>You have agreed to be the recommender handling the preprint entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> by {{articleAuthors}} (<a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>). Thank you very much for your contribution.</p>\r\n<p><strong>We remind you that you have agreed to send out 5-10 invitations to review this preprint within the next 24 h</strong>, and to send new invitations over a period of one week if necessary, until you find at least two reviewers willing to review this preprint within {{reviewDuration}}. We thank you in advance for respecting this commitment. When inviting referees for a preprint, keep in mind that a large gender, career stage and geographic diversity is desirable.</p>\r\n<p>Invitations to review can be sent using this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a>. You can also log on to the {{appName}} website and go to 'For recommenders —&gt; Preprint(s) you are handling' in the top menu, and click on the 'choose a reviewer' button.</p>\r\n<p><strong>To identify potential reviewers, you might:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>use your own network</li>\r\n<li>look at the <strong>reviewers suggested by the authors</strong> (on the recommendation page)</li>\r\n<li>look at the references section of the preprint</li>\r\n<li>use the JANE tool (<a href="https://jane.biosemantics.org/">https://jane.biosemantics.org/</a>)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>The reviews you receive should guide your decision – <strong>within 10 days of receiving the last review</strong> – as to whether to ‘Revise’, ‘Recommend’ or ‘Reject’ the preprint. As a reminder, at the end of the evaluation process, if your decision is to ‘Recommend’ this preprint, you will need to write a “recommendation” text.</p>\r\n<p>If you need assistance in any way do not hesitate to ask us.</p>\r\n<p>There is also a guide for PCI recommenders <a href="https://peercommunityin.org/2020/10/28/pci-recommender-guide/">here</a>.</p>\r\n<p>We thank you again for initiating and managing this evaluation.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>
27	#RecommenderThankForPreprintParallelSubmission	default	{{appName}}: Thank you for handling the evaluation of a preprint	Mail to recommender to thanks them for taking a preprint in charge in case of parallel submission	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>You have agreed to be the recommender handling the preprint entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> by {{articleAuthors}} (DOI <a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>). Thank you very much for your contribution.</p>\r\n<p><strong>We remind you that you have agreed to send out 5-10 invitations to review this preprint within the next 24 h</strong>, and to send out reminders and/or new invitations, over a period of one week if necessary, until you find at least two reviewers willing to review this preprint within {{reviewDuration}}. We thank you in advance for respecting this commitment. When inviting referees for a preprint, keep in mind that a large gender, career stage and geographic diversity is desirable.</p>\r\n<p>Invitations to review can be sent using this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a>. You can also log on to the {{appName}} website and go to 'For recommenders&nbsp;—&gt; Preprints you are handling' in the top menu, and click on the 'choose a reviewer' button.</p>\r\n<p>The reviews you receive should guide your decision – <strong>within 10 days of receiving the last review</strong> – as to whether to ‘Revise’, ‘Recommend’ or ‘Reject’ the preprint.</p>\r\n<p>If your decision is to ‘Recommend’ this preprint, you will need to write a “recommendation”, which will have its own DOI and be published by {{appName}} under the license CC-BY. The recommendation is a short article, similar to a News &amp; Views piece. It has its own title, contains between about 300 and 1500 words, describes the context and explains why the preprint is particularly interesting. The limitations of the preprint can also be discussed. This text also contains references (citing, at least, the preprint being recommended). All editorial correspondence (reviews, your decisions, authors' replies) relating to the preprint will also be published by {{appName}}.</p>\r\n<p>The authors have chosen to submit elsewhere in parallel. As there is a chance that the manuscript is accepted for publication elsewhere and consequently the authors might abandon the process at {{appName}}, we have the following mechanism to ensure reviewers’ work is respected and documented. If the authors abandon the process at {{appName}} after reviewers have written their reports, you should post the reviewers' reports on the {{appName}} website as recognition of the reviewers' work and in order to enable critical discussion. Note that there remains the outcome of rejection by you, wherein reports are not made public.</p>\r\n<p>There is also a <a href="https://peercommunityin.org/2020/10/28/pci-recommender-guide/">guide for PCI recommenders</a>.</p>\r\n<p>If you need assistance in any way do not hesitate to ask us.</p>\r\n<p>We thank you again for initiating and managing this evaluation.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
31	#RecommenderReviewConsidered	default	{{appName}}: Request to review accepted	Mail to recommender to indicate them that a reviewer agreed to review a preprint they are handling	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>{{reviewerPerson}} has accepted your invitation to review the preprint entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> by {{articleAuthors}} (<a href="#">{{articleDoi}}</a>), and has been sent a message indicating that this review must be posted or uploaded on the {{appName}} website before {{dueTime}}.</p>\r\n<p>This referee will receive an automatic reminder a few days before this deadline and you will receive a message notifying you of the posting of this review.</p>\r\n<p>If the review is not posted by the deadline, another automatic reminder will be sent to the referee followed by another reminder a few days after this deadline. You can change the content and sending dates of these reminders by following this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> (or by logging on to the {{appName}} website and going to 'For recommenders -&gt; Preprint(s) you are handling' in the tool bar) and then clicking on the "Actions -&gt; View email" button.</p>\r\n<p>We thank you again for managing this evaluation.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
32	#RecommenderReviewDeclined	default	{{appName}}: Request to review declined	Mail to recommender to indicate them that a reviewer declines to review a preprint they are handling	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>{{reviewerPerson}} has declined your invitation to review the preprint entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> by {{articleAuthors}} (<a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>).</p>\r\n<p><strong>If this is the first round of review</strong>, you will need to find another reviewer to obtain the two high-quality reviews required.<strong>&nbsp;From the second round of review, there is no minimum number of reviews required</strong>. You can invite additional reviewers by following this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or by logging onto the {{appName}} website and going to 'For recommenders —&gt; Preprint(s) you are handling' in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p>We thank you again for managing this evaluation.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
33	#RecommenderReviewerReviewCompleted	default	{{appName}}: Review completed	Mail to recommender to indicate them that a review has been completed	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>The review by {{reviewerPerson}} of the preprint entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> is now available.</p>\r\n<p>You can view and/or upload this review and manage your recommendation by following this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or by logging onto the {{appName}} website and going to 'For recommenders —&gt; Preprint(s) you are handling' in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p><strong>If all the reviews have now been completed</strong> and returned, <strong>we now expect you</strong>, according to your commitment as a recommender of the preprint, <strong>to make a decision within 10 days</strong>. If you need more time, please let us know by return mail.</p>\r\n<p>We remind you that this decision must be: ‘Revise’, ‘Recommend’ or ‘Reject’ the preprint.</p>\r\n<p>If you are ready to recommend,&nbsp;<strong>you do not need to submit an “Acceptation” decision</strong>. You should directly post your recommendation.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The "recommendation" is a short article, similar to a News &amp; Views piece; it has its own DOI and will be published by {{appName}} under the license CC-BY.&nbsp;It has its own title, contains between about 300 and 1500 words, describes the context and explains why the preprint is particularly interesting. The limitations of the preprint can also be discussed. This text also contains references (citing, at least, the preprint being recommended). All the editorial correspondence (reviews, your decisions, authors’ replies) relating to the preprint will also be published by {{appName}}.</p>\r\n<p>We thank you again for managing this evaluation.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
34	#ReviewerReviewReopened	default	{{appName}}: You can now modify your review	Mail to reviewer if recommender reopen the review of a reviewer	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>{{recommenderPerson}}, the recommender managing the evaluation process for the preprint entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> by {{articleAuthors}} has made your review concerning this preprint available for modification.</p>\r\n<p>You can now access this review, and edit it if necessary.</p>\r\n<p>You can view and edit your reviews by following this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or by logging onto the {{appName}} website and going to 'For contributors —&gt; My reviews' in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p>We thank you again for agreeing to review this preprint.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
35	#ReviewerThankForReviewAcceptation	default	{{appName}}: Thank you for agreeing to review a preprint!	Mail to a reviewer to thanks them for agreeing to review a preprint	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>Thank you very much for agreeing to review the preprint entitled "<strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong>" (<a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>). To provide a quick turnaround for the authors, please complete your review within {{reviewDuration}} (by <strong>{{dueTime}}</strong>). If you cannot get it done by then, please let us know.</p>\r\n<p>To view, write, upload and manage your review, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or log onto the {{appName}} website and go to ‘For contributors —&gt; Your reviews’ in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p>Important: guidelines for PCI reviewers can be found <a title="guideline for reviewers" href="https://peercommunityin.org/2020/10/22/pci-reviewer-guide/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>&nbsp;and a series of questions to help you conduct your review can be found <a href="https://peercommunityin.org/2022/05/20/questionnaire-for-reviewers/">here</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Please note that for reasons of transparency, your review will be sent to the authors in its entirety, and no part of the review will be sent privately to the recommender, as is common practice in journals.</p>\r\n<p>Thanks in advance for the time spent evaluating this preprint! We look forward to reading your review.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
36	#ReviewerThankForReviewDone	default	{{appName}}: Thank you for evaluating a preprint	Mail to reviewer to thanks them for their review	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>Thank you for evaluating the preprint entitled "<strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong>" by {{articleAuthors}}. Your evaluation has been sent to the recommender handling this preprint ({{recommenderPerson}}).</p>\r\n<p>You can use this message as proof of your work for {{appName}} and you can view your review at <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a>. Your review, together with the other reviews of this preprint, will guide the decision of the recommender as to whether to ‘Revise’, ‘Recommend’ or ‘Reject’ this preprint.</p>\r\n<p>Remember that if the article is recommended, all the editorial correspondence (reviews, including yours, the decisions reached by the recommender, and the authors’ replies) and a recommendation text will be published by {{appName}}, under the CC-BY licence. If, after one or several rounds of review, the recommender eventually rejects the preprint, the editorial correspondence will be sent to the authors but will NOT be published. You will be notified by e-mail at each stage in the procedure.</p>\r\n<p>{{parallelText}} If the recommender asks the authors to revise their preprint, they may invite you to evaluate their responses and the changes they have made to the preprint. If required, we therefore hope that you will be willing to take part in a second round of review.</p>\r\n<p>If you decided NOT to remain anonymous, your name will be passed on to the authors and, if the recommender decides to recommend this preprint, your name will be visible and associated with your review on the {{appName}} website. If you wish to change your mind and remain anonymous, please send a message to {{appContactMail}}, to let the members of the Managing Board know (they will make the necessary changes).</p>\r\n<p>We thank you again for supporting Peer Community In by reviewing this article!</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Your feedback matters.</strong> Please take 5 minutes to leave anonymous feedback about your experience of the evaluation by PCI: <a href="https://peercommunityin.org/your-feedback-matters">https://peercommunityin.org/your-feedback-matters</a> (passw o rd= feedback_@PCI). Feedback helps us understand what we’re doing well, what we could do better, and how we can improve and innovate the review process.</span></p>\r\n<p>Best wishes,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
37	#ReviewersArticleRecommended	default	{{appName}}: Decision on a preprint you reviewed	Mail to reviewers to indicate them that the preprint they review is now recommended	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>The article that you kindly reviewed for {{appName}} is now recommended. The recommendation of this article - along with your reviews - is now posted on {{appName}} website.</p>\r\n<p>You can find it there: <a href="{{recommDOI}}">{{recommDOI}}</a></p>\r\n<p>And there: <a href="{{linkRecomm}}">{{linkRecomm}}</a></p>\r\n<p>Do not hesitate to share the news as much as possible: social networks if you are on them, mailing, websites, CV, quotation, etc... Thanks again for reviewing this article for {{appName}}.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
38	#ReviewersArticleStatusChanged	default	{{appName}}: Decision on a preprint you reviewed	Mail to reviewers to indicate the change of the status of the preprint they reviewed	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>You have agreed to review the preprint entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong>. The status of this preprint is now: {{articleStatus}}. To view your review, the reviews of the other referees and the decision taken by the recommender, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or login to the {{appName}} website and go to 'For contributors —&gt; My reviews' in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p>We thank you for the time spent evaluating this preprint.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
39	#ReviewersArticleCancellation	default	{{appName}}: About our request to act as reviewer for a preprint	Mail to reviewers to indicate that them that the submitter cancelled their submission	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>The submission of the preprint entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> by {{articleAuthors}} has been cancelled by the author. Therefore, the recommendation process is closed. Thank you anyway for your help.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p><span style="padding-left: 1in;">{{recommenderPerson}}</span></p>
41	#SubmitterAwaitingSubmission	default	{{appName}}: Decision concerning your submission	Mail to submitter to indicate the need to revise their preprint	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>Your article, entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong>, has now been reviewed.</p>\r\n<p>The referees' comments and the recommender’s decision are shown below. As you can see, the recommender found your article very interesting but suggests certain revisions.</p>\r\n<p>We shall, in principle, be happy to recommend your article as soon as it has been revised in response to the points raised by the referees.</p>\r\n<p>When revising your article, we remind you that your article must contain the following sections (see our Guide for Authors in the Help section of the {{appName}} website):</p>\r\n<p>1) <strong>Data, script and code availability (if applicable)</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Data, statistical scripts, command lines and simulation code must be made available to readers</strong>. They should either be included in the article or deposited <strong>in </strong>an open repository such as Zenodo <strong>with a DOI</strong>. A perennial URL can be provided if no DOI is available; please note that GitHub URL are not perennial.</li>\r\n<li><strong>If deposited in </strong>an open repository, a reference to <strong>Data, statistical scripts, command lines and simulation code</strong>, with a DOI or a perennial URL, must be provided in the reference list and in the "Data, script and code availability" section</li>\r\n<li>The "Data, script and code availability" section must clearly indicate&nbsp;<strong>where and how</strong>&nbsp;data can be accessed.</li>\r\n<li>Wherever possible, data, scripts and code should be provided in machine-readable formats. Avoid PDFs other than for textual supplementary information.</li>\r\n<li>Metadata should accompany the data, to make the data understandable and reusable by the reader.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;2) <strong>Supplementary information (if applicable)</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Supplementary information (text, tables, figures, videos, etc.) can be referred to in the article. It must be available in an open repository (such as Zenodo, Dryad, OSF, Figshare, Morphobank, Morphosource, Github, MorphoMuseuM, Phenome10k, etc. or any institutional repository, etc...) with a DOI. A perennial URL can be provided if no DOI is available.</li>\r\n<li>A reference to the supplementary information, with a DOI or a perennial URL, must be provided in the reference list and in the "Supplementary information" section.</li>\r\n<li>List all documents attached to the manuscript as Supplementary Information in the "Supplementary Information" section.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>3) <strong>Funding (mandatory)</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>All sources of funding must be listed in a separate “Funding section”. The absence of funding must be clearly indicated in this section.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>4) <strong>Conflict of interest disclosure (mandatory)</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Authors should declare any potential non-financial conflict of interest (financial conflicts of interest are forbidden, see&nbsp;<a href="https://peercommunityin.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">the PCI code of conduct</a>).</li>\r\n<li>In the absence of competing interests, the authors should add the following sentence to the “Conflict of interest disclosure” section: “The authors declare they have no conflict of interest relating to the content of this article.” If appropriate, this disclosure may be completed by a sentence indicating that some of the authors are PCI recommenders: “XXX is a recommender for PCI XX.”</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>5) <strong>Materials and methods (mandatory)</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Details of experimental procedures and quantitative analyses must be made&nbsp;<strong>fully available</strong>&nbsp;to readers, in the text, as appendices, or as Supplementary Information deposited in an open repository, such as Zenodo, Dryad or institutional repositories with a DOI.</li>\r\n<li>For specimen-based studies,&nbsp;<strong>complete repository information</strong>&nbsp;should be provided and institutional abbreviations should be listed in a dedicated subsection (if applicable). Specimens on which conclusions are based&nbsp;<strong>must be deposited in an accessible and permanent repository</strong>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>When your revised article is ready, please:</p>\r\n<p>1) Upload the new version of your manuscript onto your favorite open archive and <strong>wait until it appears online</strong>;</p>\r\n<p>2) Follow this link {{linkTarget}} or logging onto the {{appName}} website and go to 'For Contributors -&gt; Your submitted preprints' in the top menu&nbsp;and <strong>click on the blue ‘VIEW/EDIT' button at the right end of the line</strong> referring to the preprint in question.</p>\r\n<p>3) Click on the black ‘EDIT YOUR ARTICLE DATA’ button (mandatory step). You can then edit the title, authors, DOI, abstract, keywords, disciplines, and DOI/URL of data, scripts and code. Do not forget to save your modifications by clicking on the green button.</p>\r\n<p>4) Click on the blue ‘EDIT YOUR REPLY TO THE RECOMMENDER’ button (mandatory step). You could then write or paste your text, upload your reply as a PDF file, and upload a document with the modifications marked in TrackChange mode. If you are submitting the final formatted version ready to be recommended, you should only add a sentence indicating that you posted the final version on the preprint server. Do not forget to <strong>save your modifications by clicking on the green button</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>5) Click on the green ‘SEND RESUBMISSION’ button. This will result in your submission being sent to the recommender.</p>\r\n<p>Once the recommender has read the revised version, they may decide to recommend it directly, in which case the editorial correspondence (reviews, recommender’s decisions, authors’ replies) and a recommendation text will be published by {{appName}} under the license CC-BY.</p>\r\n<p>Alternatively, other rounds of reviews may be needed before the recommender reaches a favorable conclusion. They may also reject your article, in which case the reviews and decision will be sent to you, but they will not be published or publicly released by {{appName}}. They will be safely stored in our database, to which only the Managing Board has access. You will be notified by e-mail at each stage in the procedure.</p>\r\n<p>We thank you in advance for submitting your revised version.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}<br><br>{{recommendationProcess}}</p>
42	#SubmitterCancelledSubmission	default	{{appName}}: Cancellation of your submission	Mail to submitter to acknowledge the cancellation of their preprint	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>The submission of your preprint entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> has been cancelled. We respect your decision, and hope that you will submit other preprints to {{appDescription}} ({{appName}}) in the near future.</p>\r\n<p>{{parallelText}}</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
43	#SubmitterNotConsideredSubmission	default	{{appName}}: Decision concerning your submission	Mail to submitter to indicate that their preprint has not been considered for evaluation	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},<br><br>You have submitted your preprint entitled&nbsp;<strong data-stringify-type="bold">{{articleTitle}}</strong>&nbsp;to {{appName}}.<br><br>Unfortunately, your preprint will not be considered for evaluation either because it is not in the scope of {{appName}} or because no recommender has initiated this evaluation since the request was made {{unconsider_limit_days}} days ago. This does not necessarily mean that your preprint is not of sufficient quality and/or interest. However, we suggest that you do not wait any longer for a return from us at this stage.<br><br>We are sorry to bring disappointing news and hope that you will consider submitting other preprints to {{appName}} in the future.<br><br>Yours sincerely,<br>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
44	#SubmitterParallelPreprintUnderConsideration	default	{{appName}}: Consideration of your preprint	Mail to submitter that a recommender took their preprint in charge in case of parallel submission	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>You have submitted your preprint entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> to {{appName}}. We are pleased to inform you that a {{appName}} recommender has initiated the evaluation process.</p>\r\n<p>At this stage of the process, your article will be sent to several referees, to ensure that at least two high-quality reviews are obtained. Based on this review, the recommender will reject, recommend or ask you to modify your article and to respond to the questions and points raised by the reviewers. The mean time to this first decision is about {{recomm_limit_days}} days.</p>\r\n<p>If after one or several rounds of reviews, the recommender handling your preprint reaches a favorable conclusion, all the editorial correspondence (reviews, recommender’s decisions, authors’ replies) and a recommendation text will be published by {{appName}} under the license CC-BY. If recommended by {{appName}}, your preprint will become an article that may be used and cited like any ‘classic’ article published in a peer-reviewed journal.</p>\r\n<p>Alternatively, if the recommender decides not to recommend your article, the reviews and the decision will be sent to you, but they will not be published or publicly released by {{appName}}. They will be safely stored in our database, to which only the Managing Board has access. You will be notified by e-mail at each stage of the procedure.</p>\r\n<p>You have selected the option of submitting elsewhere in parallel. We encourage you to finish the peer-review process with {{appName}} even if your manuscript is accepted for publication elsewhere. Please note that if this does happen and you abandon the process with {{appName}} after reviewers have contributed their time toward evaluation, we will post the reviewers' reports on the {{appName}} website as recognition of the reviewers' work and in order to enable critical discussion. If you do not agree with this, please consider cancelling your submission now, before reviewers are recruited.</p>\r\n<p>To view your submission, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or log onto the {{appName}} website and go to 'For contributors —&gt; Your submitted preprints' in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p>We thank you again for your submission.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
45	#SubmitterParallelPreprintSubmitted	default	{{appName}}: Submission of your preprint	Mail to submitter to indicate the validation of their submission in case of parallel submission	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>Thank you for submitting your preprint entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong>, to {{appDescription}} ({{appName}}).</p>\r\n<p>If you have not already done so, please suggest recommenders who could initiate the evaluation of your preprint. A recommender is very similar to a journal editor (responsible for finding reviewers, collecting reviews, and making editorial decisions based on reviews), and may eventually recommend your preprint after one or several rounds of reviews.</p>\r\n<p>Please remember that {{appName}} is under no obligation to consider your preprint. We cannot guarantee that your preprint will be reviewed, but all possible efforts will be made to make this possible. You will be notified by Email if a {{appName}} recommender decides to start the peer-review process for your preprint.</p>\r\n<p>If after one or several rounds of reviews, the recommender handling your preprint reaches a favorable conclusion, all the editorial correspondence (reviews, recommender’s decisions, authors’ replies) and a recommendation text will be published by {{appName}} under the license CC-BY. If recommended by {{appName}}, your preprint will become an article that may be used and cited like any ‘classic’ article published in a peer-reviewed journal.</p>\r\n<p>Alternatively, if the recommender decides not to recommend your article, the reviews and the decision will be sent to you, but they will not be published or publicly released by {{appName}}. They will be safely stored in our database, to which only the Managing Board has access. You will be notified by Email at each stage of the procedure.</p>\r\n<p>You have selected the option of submitting elsewhere in parallel. We encourage you to finish the peer-review process with {{appName}} even if your manuscript is accepted for publication elsewhere. Please note that if this does happen and you abandon the process with {{appName}} after reviewers have contributed their time toward evaluation, we will post the reviewers' reports on the {{appName}} website as recognition of the reviewers' work and in order to enable critical discussion. If you do not agree with this, please consider cancelling your submission now, before reviewers are recruited.</p>\r\n<p>To view your submission, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or log onto the {{appName}} website and go to 'For contributors —&gt; Your submitted preprints' in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p>We thank you again for your submission.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
46	#SubmitterPreprintStatusChanged	default	{{appName}}: Change in the status of your preprint	Mail to submitter if there is a change in the status of their preprint	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>The status of your preprint entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> has changed from "{{tOldStatus}}" to "{{tNewStatus}}".</p>\r\n<p>You can view, edit or cancel your submission by following this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or by logging onto the {{appName}} website and going to 'For contributors —&gt; Your submitted preprints' in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p>We thank you again for your submission.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
47	#SubmitterPreprintUnderConsideration	default	{{appName}}: Consideration of your preprint	Mail to submitter that a recommender took their preprint in charge	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>You have submitted your preprint entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> to {{appName}}. We are pleased to inform you that a {{appName}} recommender has initiated the evaluation process.</p>\r\n<p>At this stage of the process, your article will be sent to several referees, to ensure that at least two high-quality reviews are obtained. Based on this review, the recommender will reject, recommend or ask you to modify your article and to respond to the questions and points raised by the reviewers. The mean time to this first decision is about {{recomm_limit_days}} days.</p>\r\n<p>We remind you that this preprint must not be submitted for publication elsewhere until its evaluation by {{appName}} is complete.</p>\r\n<p>If after one or several rounds of reviews, the recommender handling your preprint reaches a favorable conclusion, all the editorial correspondence (reviews, recommender’s decisions, authors’ replies) and a recommendation text will be published by {{appName}} under the license CC-BY. If recommended by {{appName}} your preprint will become an article that may be used and cited like any ‘classic’ article published in a peer-reviewed journal.</p>\r\n<p>Alternatively, if the recommender decides not to recommend your article, the reviews and the decision will be sent to you, but they will not be published or publicly released by {{appName}}. They will be safely stored in our database, to which only the Managing Board has access. You will be notified by e-mail at each stage in the procedure.</p>\r\n<p>To view or cancel your submission, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or log onto the {{appName}} website and go to 'For contributors —&gt; Your submitted preprints' in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p>We thank you again for your submission.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
48	#SubmitterRecommendedPreprint	default	{{appName}}: Recommendation of your preprint	Mail to submitter to indicate the recommandation of their preprint	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>We are pleased to inform you that recommendation of your article <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> has now been published by {{appName}} with the editorial correspondence (reviews, author’s responses, and recommender’s decisions).</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">You can find it using its DOI:</span>&nbsp;{{doiRecomm}}</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">And its URL</span>: {{linkTarget}}</p>\r\n<p>Note that it may take up to two days before the DOI of the recommendation becomes functional.</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Do not hesitate to share the news as much as possible: social networks if you are on them, mailing, websites, CV, quotation, etc...</span></p>\r\n<p>It is very important that you follow the instructions below:</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">We now kindly ask you to add the {{appName}} badge on the 1st page of your article pdf and upload it to the preprint server as a new version. This will indicate that your article has been peer-reviewed and recommended by {{appName}}. Please add a hyperlink on the badge pointing to {{doiRecomm}}. This can be done by pasting the badge on the 1st page of your source file, creating a hyperlink, and then saving the file as a pdf. It can also be done directly on the pdf file with a pdf editing software.</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><br></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">You will find the {{appName}} badge<span style="font-weight: 400;" data-mce-fragment="1">, instructions</span>​ and an example of a PDF on this page </span><a href="https://peercommunityin.org/badges"><span style="font-weight: 400;">https://peercommunityin.org/badges</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">. You will need to enter this pas sw ord: badges_@PCI</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">If you consider publishing your preprint in a journal, </span><strong>after adding the badge to a new version of your preprint</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">, you can either:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">1) </span><strong>publish it in Peer Community Journal </strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">(</span><a href="http://peercommunityjournal.org/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">http://peercommunityjournal.org</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">) as is, in open access and at no cost.</span></p>\r\n<p>To do this, please&nbsp;format your article according to the instructions <a href="https://peercommunityjournal.org/page/instructions/#4">https://peercommunityjournal.org/page/instructions/#4</a></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">If you have any problem with the instructions and with the formatting of your article, please contact us at </span><a href="mailto:contact@peercommunityjournal.org"><span style="font-weight: 400;">contact@peercommunityjournal.org</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">- then go to </span><a href="https://peercommunityjournal.org/submit"><span style="font-weight: 400;">https://peercommunityjournal.org/submit</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, login or create an account.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">In this editorial platform of Peer Community Journal, you will need to fill out a submission form with:</span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">the doi or the URL of your preprint;</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">the doi of the PCI recommendation: {{doiRecomm}}</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">the title;</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">authors' details (first name, last name, affiliation, corresponding author or not, email address if corresponding author, ORCID (optional));</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">the abstract;</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">the PDF file of your article without the title, names, and abstract, starting at the introduction;</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1">\r\n<div><span style="font-weight: 400;">an illustration image (png, jpg, landscape, less than 500 ko).</span></div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">the editable source file of your article (docx, odt, zipped latex files, ...) used to generate the PDF of your article;</span></li>\r\n<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">a bib export file of your reference manager software containing only the references cited in your article (or, if not available, a txt file containing only the list of the dois of all your references).</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">OR</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;"><br></span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><br></span><span style="font-weight: 400;">2) </span><strong>submit it to a PCI-friendly journal</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">. The list of PCI-friendly journals, their economic model, and the conditions for submission can be found in a table at </span><a href="https://peercommunityin.org/pci-friendly-journals/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">https://peercommunityin.org/pci-friendly-journals/</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">We advise you to indicate in the cover letter to the editor:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">-that your article has already been peer-reviewed and recommended by PCI, with the link - {{doiRecomm}}&nbsp;- to the recommendation of your preprint;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">-the names of the recommender and of the reviewers (if available);</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">-that the journal is PCI-friendly;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">-that {{appName}} can pass confidentially the names of the anonymous reviewers if required (the journal must send a request to {{appContactMail}});</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">-the policy of the journal toward PCI-recommended articles (as indicated in the list of PCI-friendly journals table of </span><a href="https://peercommunityin.org/pci-friendly-journals/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">https://peercommunityin.org/pci-friendly-journals/</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">).</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">We also advise you to join to your cover letter a PDF export of the PCI recommendation webpage.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">If you submit your article to a PCI-friendly journal, then we kindly ask you to add a sentence in the acknowledgments of the article stating that "A preprint version of this article has been peer-reviewed and recommended by {{appName}} ({{doiRecomm}})."</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">OR</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;"><br></span><span style="font-weight: 400;">3) </span><strong>submit it to another journal</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">. We advise you to explain that your article has already been peer-reviewed and recommended by PCI in the cover letter to the editor and to indicate the name of the recommender and of the reviewers (if available), with the link - {{doiRecomm}} - to the recommendation of your preprint. We also advise you to join to your cover letter a PDF export of the PCI recommendation webpage. You can tell the editor-in-chief that {{appName}} can pass confidentially the names of the anonymous reviewers if required (the journal must send a request to {{appContactMail}}).</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">If you submit your article to another journal, then we kindly ask you to add a sentence in the acknowledgments of the article stating that "A preprint version of this article has been peer-reviewed and recommended by {{appName}} ({{doiRecomm}})."</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">If you have any problems, send us an Email at <a href="mailto:contact@peercommunityin.org">contact@peercommunityin.org</a></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Your feedback matters.</strong> Please take 5 minutes to leave anonymous feedback about your experience of the evaluation by PCI: <a href="https://peercommunityin.org/your-feedback-matters">https://peercommunityin.org/your-feedback-matters</a> (passw o rd= feedback_@PCI). Feedback helps us understand what we’re doing well, what we could do better, and how we can improve and innovate the review process.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Thank you for using {{appName}}. We hope that you will submit other preprints in the future and will tell your colleagues about {{appName}}.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;"><br></span><span style="font-weight: 400;">Yours sincerely,</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The Managing Board of {{appName}}</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">&nbsp;</span></p>
49	#SubmitterRejectedSubmission	default	{{appName}}: Decision concerning your submission	Mail to submitter to indicate the rejection of their preprint	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>Your preprint entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> has been evaluated by at least two referees. On the basis of these reviews, we regret to inform you that the {{appName}} recommender in charge of this evaluation has decided not to recommend it.</p>\r\n<p>The reviews and the recommender’s decision are shown below. These reviews and the decision will not be published or publicly released by {{appName}}. They will be safely stored in our database, to which only the Managing Board has access.</p>\r\n<p>We are sorry to bring disappointing news and hope that you will consider submitting other preprints to {{appName}} in the future.</p>\r\n<p>We thank you again for your submission.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}<br><br>{{recommendationProcess}}</p>
50	#SubmitterPreprintSubmitted	default	{{appName}}: Your submission	Mail to submitter to indicate the validation of their submission	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},<br><br>We have validated your submission to {{longname}}.</p>\r\n<div>We have sent a message to all recommenders of {{appName}} you may have suggested to let them know about this submission. You will be notified by e-mail if a recommender decides to start the peer-review process for your preprint. If none of them decide to act as a recommender, you'll receive an e-mail inviting you to suggest additionnal recommenders (we can also make suggestions if you wish).&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><br>We remind you that this preprint must not be published or submitted for publication elsewhere. If this preprint is taken in charge by a recommender and therefore sent out for review, you must not submit it to a journal until the evaluation process is complete (ie until it has been rejected or recommended by {{appName}}).</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>To view or cancel your submission, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or logging onto the {{appName}} website and go to 'For contributors —&gt; Your submitted preprints' in the top menu. As long as a recommender has not picked up your submitted article, you can also suggest additional recommenders.<br><br>We thank you again for your submission.<br><br>Yours sincerely,<br><br>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</div>
51	#TestMail	default	{{appName}}: Test Mail	Mail test	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>This is a test message; please ignore.</p>
53	#DefaultReviewCancellation	default	{{appName}}: Cancellation of a review request	Mail to reviewer to indicate them a cancellation to review a preprint	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p>You were invited to act as a reviewer for a preprint entitled "{{art_title}}" by {{art_authors}} (<a href="%7b%7bart_doi%7d%7d">{{art_doi}}</a>).</p>\r\nThis invitation is cancelled either because you did not reply to the invitation, or because we now have enough reviews for this preprint.<br>Consequently, this preprint no longer appears in your list of requests to act as a reviewer on the {{longname}} webpage.</div>\r\n<p>I apologize for any inconvenience and wish you all the best.</p>\r\n<p>Best regards,</p>\r\n<p>{{sender}}</p>
54	#DefaultReviewInvitationRegisteredUser	default	{{appName}}: Invitation from {{senderName}} to review a manuscript	Mail to user already registered to indicate them that they are invited to review a preprint 	<p style="text-align: justify;">Dear Dr. {{LastName}},</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">This is an invitation to review for </span><a href="https://peercommunityin.org/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Peer Community In</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> (PCI), a non-profit, non-commercial initiative, bolstered by the support of more than <a href="https://peercommunityin.org/pci-network/">150 respected research organizations from over 20 countries</a>.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">A manuscript, titled “<strong>{{art_title}}</strong>” by {{authors}}, has been submitted to {{longname}} and is available here: <a href="{{art_doi}}">{{art_doi}}</a>. I kindly request your assistance in evaluating this work within {{reviewDuration}}, though extensions can be accommodated if needed.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">If you accept the invitation, you can choose to sign your review or remain anonymous.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Should the manuscript be accepted, your review will be published by {{longname}}, and I will write a short text explaining the article’s quality. If the manuscript is rejected, reviews are simply conveyed to the authors.</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><br></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Once accepted, the authors can then leave it on the preprint server as a PCI-recommended preprint. They can also decide to publish it directly in the <a href="https://peercommunityjournal.org">Peer Community Journal</a> (Diamond Open Access) or submit it for publication to one of the <a href="https://peercommunityin.org/pci-friendly-journals/">PCI-friendly journals</a>.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Importantly, you should not accept this invitation if you have any conflict of interest with the authors (i.e., if you were part of the same research team, regularly co-published, or shared joint funding during the last four years).</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><br></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Note that your login to {{longname}} is the email address that we used to contact you.</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><br></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">It’s possible that reviewing for PCI might not align with your current priorities or time constraints. Should this be the case, please rest assured that I fully comprehend your choice.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Thank you in advance for your help.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Best wishes,</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">{{sender}}, {{Institution}}, {{country}}</span></p>
55	#DefaultReviewInvitationNewUser	default	{{appName}}: Invitation from {{senderName}} to review a manuscript	Mail to user not yet registered to indicate them that they are invited to review a preprint	<p style="text-align: justify;">Dear Dr. {{LastName}},</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">This is an invitation to review for </span><a href="https://peercommunityin.org/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Peer Community In</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> (PCI), a non-profit, non-commercial initiative, bolstered by the support of more than <a href="https://peercommunityin.org/pci-network/">150 respected research organizations from over 20 countries</a>.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">A manuscript, titled “<strong>{{art_title}}</strong>” by {{authors}}, has been submitted to {{longname}} and is available here: <a href="{{art_doi}}">{{art_doi}}</a>. I kindly request your assistance in evaluating this work within {{reviewDuration}}, though extensions can be accommodated if needed.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">If you accept the invitation, you can choose to sign your review or remain anonymous.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Should the manuscript be accepted, your review will be published by {{longname}}, and I will write a short text explaining the article’s quality. If the manuscript is rejected, reviews are simply conveyed to the authors.</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><br></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Once accepted, the authors can then leave it on the preprint server as a PCI-recommended preprint. They can also decide to publish it directly in the <a href="https://peercommunityjournal.org">Peer Community Journal</a> (Diamond Open Access) or submit it for publication to one of the <a href="https://peercommunityin.org/pci-friendly-journals/">PCI-friendly journals</a>.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Importantly, you should not accept this invitation if you have any conflict of interest with the authors (i.e., if you were part of the same research team, regularly co-published, or shared joint funding during the last four years).</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><br></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Note that your login to {{longname}} is the email address that we used to contact you.</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><br></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">It’s possible that reviewing for PCI might not align with your current priorities or time constraints. Should this be the case, please rest assured that I fully comprehend your choice.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Thank you in advance for your help.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Best wishes,</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">{{sender}}, {{Institution}}, {{country}}</span></p>
59	#ReminderSubmitterSuggestedRecommenderNeeded	default	{{appName}}: Please, suggest some recommenders for handling your preprint	Mail to submitter if they have not suggested any recommender	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},<br><br>Thank you very much for submitting your preprint to {{appName}}. Before we validate this submission, could you suggest 5 to 10 recommenders:<br><br>1) Go to <a href="{{siteUrl}}">{{siteUrl}}</a> and log in<br>2) Go to 'For contributors —&gt; Your submitted preprints' in the top menu.<br>3) Click on the black 'ADD/REMOVE' button in the middle of the line referring to the preprint in question and add or remove suggested recommenders.<br>4) Click on the green 'COMPLETE YOUR SUBMISSION' button when you have finished.<br><br>We remind you that you must not suggest recommender who might have a conflict of interest - see the PCI code of conduct: <a href="{{ethicsLink}}">{{ethicsLink}}</a>.<br><br>If you need any help suggesting recommenders or using the {{appName}} website, let us know.<br><br>Best regards</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
60	#ReminderSubmitterNewSuggestedRecommenderNeeded	default	{{appName}}: New suggested recommenders needed	Mail to submitter if the preprint is not taken in charge after 10 days	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p><br>Thanks again for submitting your preprint to {{appName}}. Despite some reminders, none of the suggested recommenders has yet decided to start the evaluation of your preprint. At this stage, we strongly suggest you to suggest additionnal recommenders as follow:<br><br>1) Go to <a href="{{siteUrl}}">{{siteUrl}}</a>&nbsp;and log in<br>2) Go to 'FOR CONTRIBUTORS —&gt; YOUR SUBMITTED PREPRINTS' in the top menu.<br>3) Click on the black 'ADD/REMOVE' button in the middle of the line referring to the preprint in question and add or remove suggested recommenders.<br>4) Click on the green 'COMPLETE YOUR SUBMISSION' button when you have finished.<br><br>Thanks in advance<br>All the best</p>\r\n<p>The managing board of {{appName}}</p>
61	#ReminderSubmitterCancelSubmission	default	{{appName}}: Submission not considered	Mail to submitter if the preprint is not taken in charge after 20 days	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>You have submitted your preprint entitled&nbsp;<strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong>&nbsp;to {{appName}}.</p>\r\n<p>Unfortunately, no recommender has initiated the evaluation of your preprint since the submission of this preprint &gt; 20 days ago. This does not mean that your preprint is not of sufficient quality and/or interest. However, we suggest that you do not wait any longer for a return from us at this stage and therefore to cancel your submission by:</p>\r\n<p>1) Logging onto the {{appName}} website.&nbsp;<br>2) Go to 'FOR CONTRIBUTORS' —&gt; 'YOUR SUBMITTED PREPRINTS' in the top menu.<br>3) Click on the black 'VIEW/EDIT' button at the right end of the line referring to the preprint in question.<br>4) Click on the orange 'I WISH TO CANCEL MY SUBMISSION’ button.</p>\r\n<p>We are sorry to bring disappointing news and hope that you will consider submitting other preprints to {{appName}} in the future.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
62	#ReminderSuggestedRecommenderInvitation	default	{{appName}}: Request to act as a recommender for a preprint - reminder	Mail to suggested recommenders to remind them to act as recommender of a submitted preprint	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>A few days ago, {{articleAuthors}} suggested you as a recommender for their preprint entitled&nbsp;<strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong>: <a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Very important: </strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>You should agree to become the recommender for this preprint only if, after reading it, you think that it is interesting and merits evaluation</strong> (relevant research question, quality of the methods/data/analysis, etc.).</p>\r\n<p>You can obtain information about this request and accept or decline this invitation by following this link&nbsp;<a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a>&nbsp;or by logging on to the {{appName}} website and going to 'For recommenders —&gt; Request(s) to handle a preprint' in the tool bar.</p>\r\n<p>The article has been adjudged to lie within the scope of the PCI, but there was no scientific filtering by the managing board. It may, therefore, be of poor scientific quality and, if this is the case, it would be better to reject it at this stage, without peer review. So, <strong>if you feel that this preprint is of insufficient quality, please decline this request to handle it</strong>.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Important information before you agree to become the recommender for this preprint:</strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The role of a recommender is very similar to that of a journal editor (finding reviewers, collecting reviews, taking editorial decisions based on reviews). The decision to ‘Revise’, ‘Recommend’ or ‘Reject’ the preprint is based on the recommender’s evaluation. A preprint recommended by {{appName}} is an article that may be used and cited like the ‘classic’ articles published in peer-reviewed journals. The normal outcome is, therefore, to leave the preprints on preprint servers or open repositories. However, the authors of a PCI-recommended article may prefer:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>To publish their article in the Peer Community journal as is, immediately and at no cost</li>\r\n<li>To submit it to a PCI-friendly journal (acceptance with no further peer review OR response within 5 days OR use of the PCI evaluation if appropriate).</li>\r\n<li>To submit it to another journal.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Details about the recommendation process can be found&nbsp;<a href="https://peercommunityin.org/2020/10/28/pci-recommender-guide/">here</a>.</p>\r\n<p>By agreeing to become the recommender for this preprint, you agree to do your best to handle the peer-review process in as short a period as possible for the authors. Indeed, this rapid turnaround time is a key factor for the success of PCI as a credible alternative to journals.</p>\r\n<p>To this end, we need you:</p>\r\n<p>1-&nbsp;<strong>To send invitations to 5-10 potential reviewers as soon as possible (e.g. within the next 24 hours)</strong><strong> </strong>and then to send out new invitations until you find at least two reviewers willing to review the preprint. Sending multiple invitations increases the chances of finding available reviewers and keeping the turnaround time short. You may, of course, use whichever strategy you prefer to invite reviewers. The key thing is to avoid situations in which only a couple of invitations are sent out in 20 days, with only one reply after 30 days.<br>2-&nbsp;<strong>To post your decision,</strong>&nbsp;ideally <strong>within 10 days</strong>&nbsp;of receiving the reviews. <br>3-&nbsp;<strong>To write a recommendation text </strong><strong>(i.e. a text of 300 to 1,500 words describing the context and explaining why</strong> the preprint is particularly interesting)&nbsp;if you decide to recommend this preprint for {{appName}} at the end of the evaluation process, and to submit it as soon as possible after deciding to recommend the article.<br>4-&nbsp;<strong>To declare that you have no conflict of interest with the authors or the content of the article.</strong>&nbsp; See the <a href="https://peercommunityin.org/">code of conduct</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Details about the recommendation process can be found&nbsp;<a href="https://peercommunityin.org/2020/10/28/pci-recommender-guide/">here</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Thank you for your help.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
68	#ReminderRecommenderRevisedDecisionSoonDue	default	{{appName}}: Editorial decision	Mail to recommender to indicate a decision soon due about the revised version	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>A few days ago, you should have received the authors' response, a tracked changes version and the link to a revised version of their article on the {{articleTitle}} by {{articleAuthors}}. We hope you have received all these documents.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>For this new round of evaluation, you must reach a decision to ‘Revise’, ‘Recommend’ or ‘Reject’ the article.</p>\r\n<p>Our advice is <strong>to make your decision directly, if possible, using the previous reviews and the author’s resubmission letter</strong>. In this case, we expect to receive your decision within the next 3 days. If you need more time, please let us know by return mail.</p>\r\n<p>If you feel that you need to send the revised version for a second round of peer review, you will need to re-invite the reviewers (please see the <a href=".../help/help_practical">"how to?" section</a> of the website).</p>\r\n<p>If you decide to recommend this preprint, you will need to write a "recommendation" that will have its own DOI and will be published by {{appName}} under the license CC-BY. The recommendation is a short article, similar to a News &amp; Views piece. It has its own title, contains between about 300 and 1500 words, describes the context and explains why the preprint is particularly interesting. The limitations of the preprint can also be discussed. This text also contains references (citing, at least, the preprint being recommended). All the editorial correspondence (reviews, your decisions, authors’ replies) relating to the preprint will also be published by {{appName}}.</p>\r\n<p>We look forward to your decision. Thanks in advance!</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
69	#ReminderRecommenderRevisedDecisionDue	default	{{appName}}: Editorial decision - reminder	Mail to recommender to indicate a decision due about the revised version	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>This is a reminder for your decision on the revised version of the preprint by {{articleAuthors}}.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>For this new round of evaluation, you must reach a decision to ‘Revise’, ‘Recommend’ or ‘Reject’ the article.</p>\r\n<p>Our advice is <strong>to make your decision directly, if possible, using the previous reviews and the author’s resubmission letter</strong>. If you need more time, please let us know by return mail.</p>\r\n<p>If you feel that you need to send the revised version for a second round of peer review, you will need to re-invite the reviewers (please see the <a href=".../help/help_practical">"how to?" section</a> of the website).</p>\r\n<p>If you decide to recommend this preprint, you will need to write a "recommendation" that will have its own DOI and will be published by {{appName}} under the license CC-BY. The recommendation is a short article, similar to a News &amp; Views piece. It has its own title, contains between about 300 and 1500 words, describes the context and explains why the preprint is particularly interesting. The limitations of the preprint can also be discussed. This text also contains references (citing, at least, the preprint being recommended). All the editorial correspondence (reviews, your decisions, authors’ replies) relating to the preprint will also be published by {{appName}}.</p>\r\n<p>We look forward to your decision. Thanks in advance!</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
70	#ReminderRecommenderRevisedDecisionOverDue	default	{{appName}}: Editorial decision overdue	Mail to recommender to indicate an overdue decision about the revised version	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>This is another reminder for your decision on the revised version of the preprint by {{articleAuthors}}.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>For this new round of evaluation, you must reach a decision to ‘Revise’, ‘Recommend’ or ‘Reject’ the article.</p>\r\n<p>Our advice is <strong>to make your decision directly, if possible, using the previous reviews and the author’s resubmission letter</strong>. If you need more time, please let us know by return mail.</p>\r\n<p>If you feel that you need to send the revised version for a second round of peer review, you will need to re-invite the reviewers (please see the <a href=".../help/help_practical">"how to?" section</a> of the website).</p>\r\n<p>If you decide to recommend this preprint, you will need to write a "recommendation" that will have its own DOI and will be published by {{appName}} under the license CC-BY. The recommendation is a short article, similar to a News &amp; Views piece. It has its own title, contains between about 300 and 1500 words, describes the context and explains why the preprint is particularly interesting. The limitations of the preprint can also be discussed. This text also contains references (citing, at least, the preprint being recommended). All the editorial correspondence (reviews, your decisions, authors’ replies) relating to the preprint will also be published by {{appName}}.</p>\r\n<p>We look forward to your decision. Thanks in advance!</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
71	#ReminderSubmitterRevisedVersionWarning	default	{{appName}}: Revised version - reminder	Mail to submitter to have some news about their revised version	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>Thanks again for submitting your preprint to {{appName}}. We really appreciate it.</p>\r\n<p>You should have received the decision of the recommender and the reviews on which they based their decision. We hope you found this feedback interesting and constructive.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>We now wait for your revised version. We expect to receive your revision within 2 months. If you need more time, just tell us.​</p>\r\n<p><strong>Additional requirements of the managing board: &nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>As indicated in the Guide for authors section, please make sure that: &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>-Data are available to readers, either in the text or through an open data repository such as Zenodo (free), Dryad (pay) or some other institutional repository. Data must be reusable, thus metadata or accompanying text must carefully describe the data. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>-Details on quantitative analyses (e.g., data treatment and statistical scripts in R, bioinformatic pipeline scripts, etc.) and details concerning simulations (scripts, code) are available to readers in the text, as appendices, or through an open data repository, such as Zenodo, Dryad or some other institutional repository. The scripts or code must be carefully described so that they can be reused. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>-Details on experimental procedures are available to readers in the text or as appendices. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>-Authors have no financial conflict of interest relating to the article. The article must contain a Conflict of interest disclosure paragraph before the reference section containing this sentence: The authors of this preprint declare that they have no financial conflict of interest with the content of this article. If appropriate, this disclosure may be completed by a sentence indicating that some of the authors are PCI recommenders: XXX is a recommender at {{appName}}.</p>\r\n<p>All the best</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>
72	#ReminderSubmitterRevisedVersionNeeded	default	{{appName}}: Revised version?	Mail to submitter to verify that they received the decision and if they intend to resubmit	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>As I am following the preprint submitted to {{appName}}, I'm wondering whether you found the time to revise your manuscript. Once again, there is no rush on our side. I am just writing to you with the concern of ensuring a good follow-up of the manuscript submitted to PCI. If you need more time, there is no problem. Just tell us an approximate date and we will adjust a possible reminder accordingly.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Additional requirements of the managing board: &nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>As indicated in the Guide for authors section, please make sure that:</p>\r\n<p>-Data are available to readers, either in the text or through an open data repository such as Zenodo (free), Dryad (pay) or some other institutional repository. Data must be reusable, thus metadata or accompanying text must carefully describe the data. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>-Details on quantitative analyses (e.g., data treatment and statistical scripts in R, bioinformatic pipeline scripts, etc.) and details concerning simulations (scripts, code) are available to readers in the text, as appendices, or through an open data repository, such as Zenodo, Dryad or some other institutional repository. The scripts or code must be carefully described so that they can be reused. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>-Details on experimental procedures are available to readers in the text or as appendices. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>-Authors have no financial conflict of interest relating to the article. The article must contain a Conflict of interest disclosure paragraph before the reference section containing this sentence: The authors of this preprint declare that they have no financial conflict of interest with the content of this article. If appropriate, this disclosure may be completed by a sentence indicating that some of the authors are PCI recommenders: XXX is a recommender at {{appName}}.</p>\r\n<p>All the best,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>\r\n<p>(this is an automatic message, but we are indeed interested in having information about the ongoing process)</p>
73	#ReminderRecommenderDecisionSoonDue	default	{{appName}}: Editorial decision	Mail to recommender to indicate a decision soon due	<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Dear </span><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">{{destPerson}}</span><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">,</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">All reviewers have posted and completed their reviews some days ago. This means that you can now write a decision text (as an Editor would do) and choose between the 3 decisions : Reject, Revise or Recommend. To post your decision on the PCI {{appName}} website, please:</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">1) Go to </span><a style="white-space: pre-wrap;" href="{{siteUrl}}">{{siteUrl}}</a><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;"> and log in&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">2) Go to 'FOR RECOMMENDERS'—&gt; 'PREPRINT(S) YOU ARE HANDLING' in the top menu. </span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">3) Click on the black 'VIEW/EDIT' button at the right end of the corresponding line. </span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">4) Click on the black 'WRITE OR EDIT YOUR DECISION / RECOMMENDATION’ button. </span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">5) Indicate your decision by selecting 'I RECOMMEND THIS PREPRINT', 'THIS PREPRINT MERITS REVISION' or 'I REJECT THIS PREPRINT'.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">6) Choose a decision or recommendation title (this is of particular importance only for decisions to recommend the preprint concerned) and write or copy/paste your decision or recommendation text.<br><strong data-stringify-type="bold">You do not need to copy-paste the comments of the reviewers in your decision&nbsp;</strong>(as the reviews are automatically attached to your decision)<br>If you are ready to recommend, you do not need to submit an "Acceptation" decision. You should directly post your recommendation<br>You can save a draft version of your decision or recommendation text by clicking on the blue 'SAVE' button (you will then have to go through steps 0 to 5 to complete your decision or recommendation). </span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">7) To send your decision or recommendation to the managing board for validation, click on the green 'SAVE AND COMPLETE' button. This will result in your decision or recommendation being sent to the managing board for validation.</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Thanks in advance.</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Best regards</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">The Managing Board of {{appName}} </span><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">{{appName}}</span></p>\r\n<p><span id="docs-internal-guid-7d7c062e-7fff-1d1b-f9f2-a4f242c7a5bf"></span></p>
74	#ReminderRecommenderDecisionDue	default	{{appName}}: Editorial decision - reminder	Mail to recommender to indicate a decision due	<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Dear </span><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">{{destPerson}}</span><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">,</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">All reviewers have posted and completed their reviews 10 days ago or more. This means that it's now time to write a decision text (as an Editor would do) and choose between the 3 decisions : Reject, Revise or Recommend. To post your decision on the PCI <span style="white-space: normal;">{{appName}}</span> website, please:</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">1) Go to </span><a style="white-space: pre-wrap;" href="{{siteUrl}}">{{siteUrl}}</a><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;"> </span><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">and log in&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">2) Go to 'FOR RECOMMENDERS'—&gt; 'PREPRINT(S) YOU ARE HANDLING' in the top menu. </span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">3) Click on the black 'VIEW/EDIT' button at the right end of the corresponding line. </span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">4) Click on the black 'WRITE OR EDIT YOUR DECISION / RECOMMENDATION’ button. </span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">5) Indicate your decision by selecting 'I RECOMMEND THIS PREPRINT', 'THIS PREPRINT MERITS REVISION' or 'I REJECT THIS PREPRINT'.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">6) Choose a decision or recommendation title (this is of particular importance only for decisions to recommend the preprint concerned) and write or copy/paste your decision or recommendation text.<br><strong data-stringify-type="bold">You do not need to copy-paste the comments of the reviewers in your decision&nbsp;</strong>(as the reviews are automatically attached to your decision).<br>If you are ready to recommend, you do not need to submit an "Acceptation" decision. You should directly post your recommendation.<br>You can save a draft version of your decision or recommendation text by clicking on the blue 'SAVE' button (you will then have to go through steps 0 to 5 to complete your decision or recommendation).</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">7) To send your decision or recommendation to the managing board for validation, click on the green 'SAVE AND COMPLETE' button. This will result in your decision or recommendation being sent to the managing board for validation.</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Thanks in advance.</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Best regards</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">The Managing Board of {{appName}} </span>{{appName}}</p>\r\n<p><span id="docs-internal-guid-7d7c062e-7fff-1d1b-f9f2-a4f242c7a5bf"></span></p>
75	#ReminderRecommenderDecisionOverDue	default	{{appName}}: Editorial decision overdue	Mail to recommender to indicate a decision overdue	<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Dear </span><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">{{destPerson}}</span><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">,</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">A kind reminder: all reviewers have posted and completed their reviews more than 10 days ago. This means that it's now time to write a decision text (as an Editor would do) and choose between the 3 decisions : Reject, Revise or Recommend. To post your decision on the PCI {{appName}} website, please:</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">1) Go to <a href="{{siteUrl}}">{{siteUrl}}</a></span><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;"> and log in&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">2) Go to 'FOR RECOMMENDERS'—&gt; 'PREPRINT(S) YOU ARE HANDLING' in the top menu. </span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">3) Click on the black 'VIEW/EDIT' button at the right end of the corresponding line. </span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">4) Click on the black 'WRITE OR EDIT YOUR DECISION / RECOMMENDATION’ button. </span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">5) Indicate your decision by selecting 'I RECOMMEND THIS PREPRINT', 'THIS PREPRINT MERITS REVISION' or 'I REJECT THIS PREPRINT'.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">6) Choose a decision or recommendation title (this is of particular importance only for decisions to recommend the preprint concerned) and write or copy/paste your decision or recommendation text.<br><strong data-stringify-type="bold">You do not need to copy-paste the comments of the reviewers in your decision&nbsp;</strong>(as the reviews are automatically attached to your decision)<br>If you are ready to recommend, you do not need to submit an "Acceptation" decision. You should directly post your recommendation.<br>You can save a draft version of your decision or recommendation text by clicking on the blue 'SAVE' button (you will then have to go through steps 0 to 5 to complete your decision or recommendation). </span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">7) To send your decision or recommendation to the managing board for validation, click on the green 'SAVE AND COMPLETE' button. This will result in your decision or recommendation being sent to the managing board for validation.</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Thanks in advance.</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Best regards</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">The Managing Board of {{appName}} </span><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">{{appName}}</span></p>\r\n<p><span id="docs-internal-guid-7d7c062e-7fff-1d1b-f9f2-a4f242c7a5bf"></span></p>
76	#ReminderReviewerReviewInvitationRegisteredUser	default	{{appName}}: Invitation from {{senderName}} to review a manuscript - reminder	Mail to user already registered to remind them that they have been invited as a reviewer	\n<p><strong>A friendly reminder of my invitation to review.</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;"> I hope you can accept, but if for any reason you must decline, please be assured that I understand your decision. In any case, a response - by clicking on the buttons below - would be greatly appreciated.<br></span><span style="font-weight: 400;">{{message}}</span></p>
77	#UserChangeMail	default	{{appName}}: validate of your new email address	Mail to user to validate its new email address	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>Please validate your new e-mail address by clicking on this link:<br><a href="{{verifyMailUrl}}">{{verifyMailUrl}}</a></p>\r\n<p>Thanks in avance</p>\r\n<p>The Managing board of {{appName}}</p>
78	#UserRecoverMail	default	{{appName}}: Your email address has been changed	Mail to user that they might revert the change of their email address	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>You recently ask to change your email address.</p>\r\n<p>If you want to cancel this email address change please follow this link :<br><a href="{{recoverMailUrl}}">{{recoverMailUrl}}</a></p>\r\n<p>Thanks</p>
79	#ReminderReviewerReviewInvitationNewUser	default	{{appName}}: Invitation from {{senderName}} to review a manuscript - reminder	Mail to user not yet registered to remind them that they have been invited as a reviewer	\n<p><strong>A friendly reminder of my invitation to review.</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;"> I hope you can accept, but if for any reason you must decline, please be assured that I understand your decision. In any case, a response - by clicking on the buttons below - would be greatly appreciated.<br></span><span style="font-weight: 400;">{{message}}</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>
80	#RecommenderPendingReviewRequest	default	{{appName}}: A putative reviewer for a preprint you are handling	Mail to recommender to indicate that a user is willing to review a preprint they are handling	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>You have initiated the evaluation of the article entitled&nbsp;<strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> by {{articleAuthors}} (<a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>).</p>\r\n<p>{{reviewerPerson}} is willing to review this preprint.</p>\r\n<p>You can accept or decline this offer by following this link:&nbsp;<a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or by logging onto the {{appName}} website and going to 'For recommenders —&gt; Preprints you are handling' in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p>We thank you for managing this evaluation.</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
81	#ReviewerReviewRequestAccepted	default	{{appName}}: Your offer to review an article has been accepted	Mail to user to indicate that the recommender has accepted their proposal to review the preprint	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},<br><br>You have indicated your willingness to review the preprint entitled {{articleTitle}} by {{articleAuthors}} (<a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>). Thanks a lot.<br><br>I have accepted your offer and I would be delighted to receive your review within {{reviewDuration}}, hence before {{dueTime}}. If this dealine is too short, please let me know as soon as possible. Otherwise, thank you in advance for respecting this deadline.<br><br>To view, write, upload and manage your review, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or log onto the {{appName}} website and go to ‘For contributors —&gt; Your reviews’ in the top menu.<br><br>When you have written or uploaded your review, you can:<br><br>1) save a draft version of your review for future modification by clicking on the ‘Save’ button; this allows you to make changes or to complete your review later;<br><br>or<br><br>2) save and send me your review by clicking on the ‘Save &amp; submit your review’ button.<br><br>If you have saved a draft version of your review, you can come back to it for modification or completion by clicking on ‘For contributors —&gt; Your reviews’ in the top menu, and then on the black ‘View/Edit’ button to the right on the corresponding line. Don’t forget to click on the ‘Save &amp; submit your review’ button to send your completed review to me.<br><br>Guidelines for PCI reviewers can be found <a href="https://peercommunityin.org/2020/10/22/pci-reviewer-guide/">here</a>.<br><br>Thanks in advance for the time spent evaluating this preprint.<br><br>I look forward to reading your review.<br><br>Yours sincerely,<br><br>The recommender, {{recommenderPerson}}</p>
82	#ReviewerReviewRequestDeclined	default	{{appName}}: Your request to review an article has been declined	Mail to user to indicate that the recommender decline their proposal to review the preprint	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},<br><br>You kindly indicated your willingness to review the preprint entitled {{articleTitle}} by {{articleAuthors}} (<a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>). However, the recommender of this preprint has declined your offer - they probably already found enough reviewers for evaluating this preprint.<br><br>We hope you'll not be too disappointed and that you'll still be interested by giving some input to {{appName}} in the near future. <br><br>Yours sincerely,<br><br>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
83	#NewsLetterMonthly	default	{{appName}}: Newsletter	Mail to users that choose to receive the newsletter once a month	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>See below for the latest updates from {{appName}}.</p>\r\n<p>Best regards,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
84	#NewsLetterEveryTwoWeeks	default	{{appName}}: Newsletter	Mail to users that choose to receive the newsletter every two weeks	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>See below for the latest updates from {{appName}}.</p>\r\n<p>Best regards,</p>\r\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
85	#SubmitterAcknowledgementSubmission	default	{{appName}}: thanks for your submission	Mail to submitter to acknowledge their submission	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>Thank you for your submission to ({{appName}}).</p>\r\n<p>If you have not already done so, please suggest recommenders who could initiate the evaluation of your preprint. A recommender is very similar to a journal editor (responsible for finding reviewers, collecting reviews, and making editorial decisions based on reviews), and may eventually recommend your preprint after one or several rounds of reviews.</p>\r\n<p>We will check that this preprint is within the scope of {{appName}} and that the data, scripts, code are publicly available. We will contact you if needed or validate your submission directly.</p>\r\n<p>In any case, we will keep you informed in the next few days.</p>\r\n<p>Thanks again for this submission</p>\r\n<p>The managing board of {{appName}}</p>
86	#AdminTwoReviewersIn	default	{{appName}}: {{recommenderPerson}} found two reviewers	Mail to admnistrators to indicate that 2 reviewers agreed to review the preprint	<p>Dear administrators of {{appName}},</p>\r\n<p>A second reviewer agreed to review the preprint "{{articleTitle}}" by {{articleAuthors}}. Other invitations to referee might be in progress but {{recommenderPerson}} could make their editorial decision based on these two reviews.</p>\r\n<p>To manage this recommendation, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Have a nice day!</p>
87	#AdminAllReviewsCompleted	default	{{appName}}: All reviews completed	Mail to administrators to indicate them that all reviews have been completed	<p>Dear administrators of {{appName}},</p>\r\n<p>All reviews of the preprint <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> by {{articleAuthors}} are completed. {{recommenderPerson}}, the recommender of this preprint can now make an editorial decision.</p>\r\n<p>To manage this recommendation, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Have a nice day!</p>
89	#AdminArticleResubmited	default	{{appName}}: Article resubmitted	Mail to MB to indicate that a revised version has been submitted and is under consideration by the recommender	<p>Dear administrators of {{appName}},</p>\r\n<p>A new version of the article entitled "{{articleTitle}}" is under consideration by {{recommenderPerson}} for {{appName}}.</p>\r\n<p>To manage this recommendation, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Have a nice day!</p>
123	#RecommenderSuggestedReviewers	default	{{appName}}: suggested reviewers	Mail to recommender to notify reviewer declined invitation and suggests alternative reviewers	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>The reviewer {{reviewerPerson}} that just declined your invitation to review the preprint entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}} </strong>suggests the following reviewers:</p>\r\n<p>{{suggestedReviewersText}}</p>\r\n<p>You can invite these reviewers by following this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or by logging onto the {{appName}} website and going to 'For recommenders —&gt; Preprint(s) you are handling’ in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p>We thank you again for managing this evaluation.</p>\r\n<p>All the best,<br>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
156	#ReviewerGenericMail	default	{{appName}}: about your peer review	Generic mail to reviewers for recommender/managers to notify any additional information	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\n<p>Regarding your review of the preprint entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong>,<br><br><br><b><em>**You can edit/write your message to the referee**</em></b><br><br><br></p>\n<p>We thank you again for evaluating this preprint.</p>\n<p>All the best,<br>{{recommenderPerson}} at {{appName}}</p>
157	#DefaultReviewAlreadyAcceptedCancellation	default	{{appName}}: About your review	Mail to reviewer to indicate them a cancellation to review a preprint	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<div>You kindly agreed to review the preprint entitled "<strong>{{art_title}}</strong>" by {{art_authors}} (<a href="{{art_doi}}">{{art_doi}}</a>).</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>I am writing to let you know that we have decided to move ahead with an editorial decision on this manuscript without your evaluation.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>If you have any questions and if you have already written your review, please feel free to reply by return email and we will include it in the evaluation. Thank you in advance.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\nBest regards,</div>\r\n<p>{{sender}}</p>
158	#ReminderReviewerInvitationNewRoundRegisteredUser	default	{{appName}}: Invitation to review a new version of a preprint you have already reviewed - reminder	Mail to user already registered to remind them that they have been invited as a reviewer	<p><strong>A kind reminder</strong><br>{{message}}</p>
159	#DefaultReviewInvitationNewRoundRegisteredUser	default	{{appName}}: Invitation to review a new version of a preprint you have already reviewed	Mail to user already registered to indicate them that they are invited to re-review a preprint	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\r\n<p>This is an invitation to review the new version of the preprint "<strong>{{art_title}}</strong>" (<a href="{{art_doi}}">{{art_doi}}</a>), for potential recommendation by {{description}} ({{longname}}).</p>\r\n<p>You have already reviewed this article in a previous round of review, and we thank you again for this helpful contribution.</p>\r\n<p>The authors’ responses to your previous comments and the tracked changes version of the manuscript are available at the bottom of this message.</p>\r\n<p>The evaluation process should guide the decision as to whether to ‘Revise’, ‘Recommend’ or ‘Reject’ the preprint.</p>\r\n<p>Please let us know if you accept or decline this invitation by clicking on the link below or by logging onto the {{longname}} website and going to 'For contributors —&gt; Invitation(s) to review a preprint' in the top menu.</p>\r\n<p>Thanks in advance for your help!</p>\r\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\r\n<p>{{sender}}</p>
161	#ReminderRecommender2ReviewsReceivedCouldMakeDecision	default	{{appName}}: Editorial decision possible	Mail to recommender to ask not to wait too long for additional reviews	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\n<p>\nA few weeks ago, you should have received a notification that two reviews have been received for {{articleTitle}} by {{articleAuthors}}. We require a minimum of two reviews for each submission, so it is possible for you to make your editorial decision now. In the event that you are still waiting for additional reviews, we would like to ask you not to wait too long so as not to delay the article handling time. If you would like to make your decision without waiting for further reviews, please cancel the reviews that are not yet in, and then you will be able to make a decision.\n</p>\n<p>Thank you very much for handling this submission.</p>\n<p>Best regards,</p>\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>\n
168	#RecommenderSuggestedReviewersAccepted	default	{{appName}}: suggested reviewer	Mail to recommender to notify reviewer declined invitation and suggests alternative reviewers	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\n<p>The reviewer {{reviewerPerson}} who just accepted your invitation to review the preprint entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> suggests the following reviewers:</p>\n<p>{{suggestedReviewersText}}</p>\n<p>You can invite these reviewers by following this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or by logging onto the {{appName}} website and going to 'For recommenders —&gt; Preprint(s) you are handling’ in the top menu.</p>\n<p>We thank you again for managing this evaluation.</p>\n<p>All the best,<br>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
201	#RecommenderRejectMail	default	{{appName}}: A feedback from a suggested recommender who declined	Recommender mail to managers explaining why they rejected an invite	<p>Dear members of the managing board,</p>\r\n<p>I've been invited to act as a recommender for the preprint entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong>, submitted by <strong>{{articleAuthors}}</strong>. I'm declining this invitation because of the following reasons:</p>\r\n<p><br><strong><em>**Please indicate these reasons here**<br><br></em></strong></p>\r\n<p>Best regards,<br>{{recommenderPerson}}</p>
203	#SubmitterGenericMail	default	{{appName}}: Revisions required to your submission	Generic mail to submitters to fix errors in their submission	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p><p>Thank you for the submission entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong>.<br><br>Before we can progress your submission, the following points need to be addressed:<br><br><br><strong>[MB member to insert points here]<br><br></strong></p><p>Please follow the steps below to revise your submission:</p><ol><li>Make the changes to the manuscript as instructed. We recommend using version control to keep the same URL to the submitted document, but if you decide to change the URL be sure to update any references to the URL in steps 3 and 4 below.</li><li>Once the revisions are made, login to the {{appName}} website and navigate to: <strong>For contributors</strong> &gt; <strong>Your submitted preprint.</strong></li><li>Find the submission that needs revising and click <strong>VIEW/EDIT.</strong></li><li>Click on “Edit preprint”. Update your submission and cover letter to respond to the points raised above and click “Save”.</li><li>Your revision has now been resubmitted for consideration by the {{appName}} Managing Board.</li></ol><p>Thanks again for your submission.</p><p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
204	#DefaultReviewInvitationNewRoundNewReviewerNewUser	default	{{appName}}: Invitation from {{senderName}} to review a manuscript	Mail to user not yet registered to indicate them that they are invited to review a preprint	<p>Dear Dr. {{LastName}},</p><p>This is an invitation to review for <a href="https://peercommunityin.org/">Peer Community In</a> (PCI), a non-profit, non-commercial initiative, bolstered by the support of more than <a href="https://peercommunityin.org/pci-network/">150 respected research organizations from over 20 countries</a>.</p><p>A manuscript, titled “{{art_title}}” by {{authors}}, has been submitted to {{longname}} and is available here: <a href="{{art_doi}}">{{art_doi}}</a>.</p><p><strong>One or several previous versions of this preprint have already been evaluated and appeared interesting</strong>. To strengthen the evaluation process, I would like to have your expert opinion on it. Would you agree to review it, possibly within {{reviewDuration}}? Extensions are possible if required, but please let us know if you need one.</p><p>If you accept the invitation, you can choose to sign your review or remain anonymous.</p><p>Should the manuscript be accepted, your review will be published by {{longname}}, and I will write a short text explaining the article’s quality. If the manuscript is rejected, reviews are simply conveyed to the authors.</p><p>Once accepted, the authors can then leave it on the preprint server as a PCI-recommended preprint. They can also decide to publish it directly in the <a href="https://peercommunityjournal.org">Peer Community Journal</a> (Diamond Open Access) or submit it for publication to one of the <a href="https://peercommunityin.org/pci-friendly-journals/">PCI-friendly journals</a>.</p><p>Importantly, you should not accept this invitation if you have any conflict of interest with the authors (i.e., if you were part of the same research team, regularly co-published, or shared joint funding during the last four years).</p><p>Note that your login to {{longname}} is the email address that we used to contact you.</p><p>It’s possible that reviewing for PCI might not align with your current priorities or time constraints. Should this be the case, please rest assured that I fully comprehend your choice.</p><p>Thank you in advance for your help.</p><p>Best wishes,</p><p>{{sender}}, {{Institution}}, {{country}}</p>
205	#DefaultReviewInvitationNewRoundNewReviewerRegisteredUser	default	{{appName}}: Invitation from {{senderName}} to review a manuscript	Mail to registered user to invite them as new reviewer to make a new round of review of a preprint	<p>Dear Dr. {{LastName}},</p><p>This is an invitation to review for <a href="https://peercommunityin.org/">Peer Community In</a> (PCI), a non-profit, non-commercial initiative, bolstered by the support of more than <a href="https://peercommunityin.org/pci-network/">150 respected research organizations from over 20 countries</a>.</p><p>A manuscript, titled “{{art_title}}” by {{authors}}, has been submitted to {{longname}} and is available here: <a href="{{art_doi}}">{{art_doi}}</a>.</p><p><strong>One or several previous versions of this preprint have already been evaluated and appeared interesting</strong>. To strengthen the evaluation process, I would like to have your expert opinion on it. Would you agree to review it, possibly within {{reviewDuration}}? Extensions are possible if required, but please let us know if you need one.</p><p>If you accept the invitation, you can choose to sign your review or remain anonymous.</p><p>Should the manuscript be accepted, your review will be published by {{longname}}, and I will write a short text explaining the article’s quality. If the manuscript is rejected, reviews are simply conveyed to the authors.</p><p>Once accepted, the authors can then leave it on the preprint server as a PCI-recommended preprint. They can also decide to publish it directly in the <a href="https://peercommunityjournal.org"> Peer Community Journal</a> (Diamond Open Access) or submit it for publication to one of the <a href="https://peercommunityin.org/pci-friendly-journals/">PCI-friendly journals</a>.</p><p>Importantly, you should not accept this invitation if you have any conflict of interest with the authors (i.e., if you were part of the same research team, regularly co-published, or shared joint funding during the last four years).</p><p>Note that your login to {{longname}} is the email address that we used to contact you.</p><p>It’s possible that reviewing for PCI might not align with your current priorities or time constraints. Should this be the case, please rest assured that I fully comprehend your choice.</p><p>Thank you in advance for your help.</p><p>Best wishes,</p><p>{{sender}}, {{Institution}}, {{country}}</p>
206	#ManagersPreprintResubmission	default	{{appName}}: Pre-submitted preprint now completed and ready for validation	Mail sent to managers on preprint resubmission	<div class="p-rich_text_section">Dear members of the Managing Board,</div><div class="p-rich_text_section"><br></div><div class="p-rich_text_section">This preprint submission by {{submitterPerson}} entitled <strong data-stringify-type="bold">{{articleTitle}}</strong> that was previously in a Pre-submission stage is now ready for validation.</div><div class="p-rich_text_section"><br></div><div class="p-rich_text_section">To check this submission, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a>.</div><div class="p-rich_text_section"><br></div><div class="p-rich_text_section"><strong data-stringify-type="bold">WARNING:</strong>&nbsp;<strong data-stringify-type="bold">do not validate it unless you (or someone else on the managing board) have checked the following points:</strong></div><ul class="p-rich_text_list p-rich_text_list__bullet" data-stringify-type="unordered-list" data-indent="0" data-border="0"><li data-stringify-indent="0" data-stringify-border="0">Files are readable, lines are numbered</li><li data-stringify-indent="0" data-stringify-border="0">DOI of (or permanent link to) the article, data, and script are correct,</li><li data-stringify-indent="0" data-stringify-border="0">Data, scripts/code, and supplementary information are available</li><li data-stringify-indent="0" data-stringify-border="0">A readme file is present with the data and script</li><li data-stringify-indent="0" data-stringify-border="0">Mandatory sections are there ("funding", "Conflict of Interest disclosure", "Data, script, code, and supplementary information availability")</li><li data-stringify-indent="0" data-stringify-border="0">No obvious financial conflicts of interest appear</li></ul><div class="p-rich_text_section">Have a nice day!</div><p><br></p>
207	#RecommenderChangeReviewDueDate	default	Recommender change due date	RecommenderChangeReviewDueDate	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\n<p>You have agreed to review the preprint entitled "<strong>{{articleTitle}}"</strong>&nbsp;(<a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>), submitted to {{appName}}, and we thank you for this contribution and for your support of PCI.</p>\n<p>The deadline for the review has been changed by the recommender. <strong>Your review is now expected by {{dueDate}}</strong>.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>To view, write, upload and manage your review, please follow this link <a href="{{myReviewsLink}}">{{myReviewsLink}}</a> or log onto the {{appName}} website and go to ‘For contributors —&gt; Your reviews’ in the top menu.</p>\n<p>Guidelines for PCI reviewers can be found <a title="guideline for reviewers" href="https://peercommunityin.org/2020/10/22/pci-reviewer-guide/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>&nbsp;and a series of questions to help you conduct your review can be found <a href="https://peercommunityin.org/2022/05/20/questionnaire-for-reviewers/">here</a>.</p>\n<p>Please note that for reasons of transparency, your review will be sent to the authors in its entirety, and no part of the review will be sent privately to the recommender, as is common practice in journals.</p>\n<p>Thanks in advance for the time and energy spent evaluating this preprint! We look forward to reading your review.</p>\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\n<p>The managing board of {{appName}}</p>
208	#ReminderRecommenderReviewersNeeded	default	{{appName}}: Please, send invitations to review the preprint you are handling	Mail to recommender to remind them to send invitation to referee	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p><p>Thanks again for taking charge of the preprint submitted by {{articleAuthors}}. We remind you that you have agreed to send out 5-10 invitations to review this preprint within the next 24h, and to send out new invitations, over a period of one week if necessary, until you manage to find at least two reviewers willing to review this preprint within {{reviewDuration}}. Thanks in advance for sending those invitations which would avoid delaying the reviewing process. To invite reviewers, please:</p><p>1) Go to <a href="{{siteUrl}}" data-mce-href="{{siteUrl}}">{{siteUrl}}</a> and log in</p><p>2) Go to 'For recommenders —&gt; Preprint(s) you are handling' in the top menu.</p><p>3) Click on the green 'INVITE A REVIEWER' button in the line corresponding to the preprint considered.</p><p>To invite a reviewer: click on the black ‘INVITE A REVIEWER’ button and complete the form (first name, last name, and e-mail address of the reviewer). You can change the subject and/or the message if you wish. Then, click on the blue 'SEND E-MAIL' button at the end of the form.</p><p>4) When you have sent invitations to all your chosen reviewers, click on the blue 'DONE 'button.</p><p><strong>To identify potential reviewers, you might:</strong></p><ul><li>use your own network</li><li>look at the reviewers suggested by the authors&nbsp;</li><li>look at the reviewers suggested by the reviewers you've already invited</li><li>look at the references section of the preprint</li><li>use the JANE tool (<a href="https://jane.biosemantics.org/" data-mce-href="https://jane.biosemantics.org/">https://jane.biosemantics.org/</a>)</li></ul><p>When inviting referees for a preprint, keep in mind that a large gender, career stage, and geographic diversity is desirable.</p><p>If you need assistance in any way do not hesitate to ask us.</p><p>Thanks in advance.</p><p>Best regards</p><p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
209	#ReminderRecommenderNewReviewersNeeded	default	{{appName}}: Please, invite additional reviewers	Mail to recommender to ask them to send new referee invitations if <2 reviewers have accepted the review invitation	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p><p>Thanks for sending invitations to review the preprint by {{articleAuthors}}. All invited reviewers have already received a reminder, but you still need to find other reviewers to be sure to obtain two reviews. Hence, we encourage you to invite further reviewers as follows:</p><p>1) Go to <a href="{{siteUrl}}" data-mce-href="{{siteUrl}}">{{siteUrl}}</a> and log in</p><p>2) Go to 'For recommenders —&gt; Preprint(s) you are handling' in the top menu.</p><p>3) Click on the green 'INVITE A REVIEWER' button in the line corresponding to the preprint considered.</p><p>To invite a reviewer: click on the black ‘INVITE A REVIEWER’ button and complete the form (first name, last name, and e-mail address of the reviewer). You can change the subject and/or the message if you wish. Then, click on the blue 'SEND E-MAIL' button at the end of the form.</p><p>4) When you have sent invitations to all your chosen reviewers, click on the blue 'DONE 'button.</p><p><strong>To identify potential reviewers, you might:</strong></p><ul><li>use your own network</li><li>look at the reviewers suggested by the authors&nbsp;</li><li>look at the reviewers suggested by the reviewers you've already invited</li><li>look at the references section of the preprint</li><li>use the JANE tool (<a href="https://jane.biosemantics.org/" data-mce-href="https://jane.biosemantics.org/">https://jane.biosemantics.org/</a>)</li></ul><p>When inviting referees for a preprint, keep in mind that a large gender, career stage, and geographic diversity is desirable.</p><p>If you need assistance in any way do not hesitate to ask us.</p><p>Thanks in advance.</p><p>Best regards</p><p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
210	#ReminderRecommenderAcceptationReview	default	{{appName}}: A reviewer agrees to review, but asks for more time - reminder	reminder delayReminder to the recommender to tell them that a reviewer agreed to review pending an extra duration time	<p><strong>A friendly reminder</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">.<br></span><span style="font-weight: 400;">{{message}}</span></p>
211	#RecommenderDeclineReviewNewDelay	default	{{appName}}: Your request for extra review duration has been declined	Email indicating the reviewer that the recommender has declined their request to have an extra delay to make their review	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\n<p>Your request for an extra review duration time to review the preprint entitled "<strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong>" has been declined by the recommender.</p>\n<p>Hence, please do not start reviewing this preprint.</p>\n<p>Thanks again for your willingness to review, and we are sorry that it does not align with the recommender's timing.</p>\n<p>We hope you'll remain motivated to review other preprints for {{appName}}.</p>\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\n<p>The managing board of {{appName}}</p>
212	#RecommenderAcceptReviewNewDelay	default	{{appName}}: Your request for extra review duration has been accepted	Mail to a reviewer to tell them that the recommender has accepted their request for an extra review duration time	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\n<p>Your request for an extra review duration time to review the preprint entitled "<strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong>" (<a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>) has been accepted by the recommender. <br><br>Hence, please complete your review within {{reviewDuration}} (i.e. by <strong>{{dueTime}}</strong>).&nbsp;</p>\n<p>To view, write, upload and manage your review, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or log onto the {{appName}} website and go to ‘For contributors —&gt; Your reviews’ in the top menu.</p>\n<p>Important: Guidelines for PCI reviewers can be found <a title="guideline for reviewers" href="https://peercommunityin.org/2020/10/22/pci-reviewer-guide/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>&nbsp;and a series of questions to help you conduct your review can be found <a href="https://peercommunityin.org/2022/05/20/questionnaire-for-reviewers/">here</a>.</p>\n<p>Please note that for reasons of transparency, your review will be sent to the authors in its entirety, and no part of the review will be sent privately to the recommender, as is common practice in journals.</p>\n<p>Thanks in advance for the time spent evaluating this preprint! We look forward to reading your review.</p>\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\n<p>The managing board of {{appName}}</p>
213	#ConditionalRecommenderAcceptationReview	default	{{appName}}: A reviewer agrees to review, but asks for more time	Mail to the recommender to tell them that a reviewer agreed to review pending an extra duration time	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\n<p>You have initiated the evaluation of the article entitled&nbsp;<strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> by {{articleAuthors}} (<a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>).</p>\n<p>You invited {{reviewerPerson}} to review this preprint. They accepted your invitation but only if the delay to review the article <strong>can be extended to {{delay}}</strong>.</p>\n<p>You can accept or decline this offer by clicking on the corresponding button below<br><br>Thanks again for managing this evaluation.</p>\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
214	#ReminderReviewerReviewDue	default	{{appName}}: Review due - reminder	Mail to reviewer to indicate a review due	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\n<p>This is a reminder for your review of the preprint "<strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong>" that is due today.</p>\n<p>To view, write, upload and manage your review, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or log onto the {{appName}} website and go to ‘For contributors —&gt; Your reviews’ in the top menu.</p>\n<p>Guidelines for PCI reviewers can be found <a title="guideline for reviewers" href="https://peercommunityin.org/2020/10/22/pci-reviewer-guide/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>&nbsp;and a series of questions to help you conduct your review can be found <a href="https://peercommunityin.org/2022/05/20/questionnaire-for-reviewers/">here</a>.</p>\n<p>Please note that for reasons of transparency, your review will be sent to the authors in its entirety, and no part of the review will be sent privately to the recommender, as is common practice in journals.</p>\n<p>In case of any problem or difficulties, or if you need an extension, please contact <a href="{{appContactMail}}">{{appContactMail}}</a>.</p>\n<p>Many thanks in advance for completing your review.</p>\n<p>Best regards</p>\n<p>The managing board of {{appName}}</p>
215	#ReminderReviewerReviewSoonDue	default	{{appName}}:  Review soon due	Mail to reviewer to indicate a review soon due	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\n<p>You have agreed to review the preprint entitled "<strong>{{articleTitle}}"</strong>&nbsp;(<a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>), submitted to {{appName}}, and we thank you for this contribution and for your support of PCI.</p>\n<p>The deadline for the review is coming up on {{reviewDueDate}}. If you need more time, please let us know by email.</p>\n<p>To view, write, upload and manage your review, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or log onto the {{appName}} website and go to ‘For contributors —&gt; Your reviews’ in the top menu.</p>\n<p>Guidelines for PCI reviewers can be found <a title="guideline for reviewers" href="https://peercommunityin.org/2020/10/22/pci-reviewer-guide/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>&nbsp;and a series of questions to help you conduct your review can be found <a href="https://peercommunityin.org/2022/05/20/questionnaire-for-reviewers/">here</a>.</p>\n<p>Please note that for reasons of transparency, your review will be sent to the authors in its entirety, and no part of the review will be sent privately to the recommender, as is common practice in journals.</p>\n<p>Thanks in advance for the time and energy spent evaluating this preprint! We look forward to reading your review.</p>\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\n<p>The managing board of {{appName}}</p>
216	#ReminderReviewerReviewOverDue	default	{{appName}}: Review overdue	Mail to reviewer to indicate a review overdue	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\n<p>This is a reminder that your review of the preprint <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong>&nbsp;was due a few days ago.</p>\n<p>We fully understand the huge number of deadlines you might face, but we also know how frustrating it can be, as an author, to wait upon reviews.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>To keep the PCI process friendly, could you please let us know (<a href="{{appContactMail}}">{{appContactMail}}</a>) when we can expect your review?</p>\n<p>To view, write, upload and manage your review, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or log onto the {{appName}} website and go to ‘For contributors —&gt; Your reviews’ in the top menu.</p>\n<p>Guidelines for PCI reviewers can be found <a title="guideline for reviewers" href="https://peercommunityin.org/2020/10/22/pci-reviewer-guide/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>&nbsp;and a series of questions to help you conduct your review can be found <a href="https://peercommunityin.org/2022/05/20/questionnaire-for-reviewers/">here</a>.</p>\n<p>Many thanks in advance for completing your review.</p>\n<p>Best regards</p>\n<p>The managing board of {{appName}}</p>
217	#ArticlePublishedPCJ	default	{{appName}}: An article you evaluated is now published in the Peer Community Journal	Mail to notify recommender and reviewers that the article has been published on PCJ	<p>Dear PCI recommender and reviewers,</p>\n<p>We are pleased to inform you that the article you reviewed and recommended for {{appName}} (<a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>) has been published in the <a href="https://peercommunityjournal.org">Peer Community Journal</a>&nbsp;(a Diamond Open Access Journal) at the request of the authors.</p>\n<p>Here is the DOI of the article now published in Peer Community Journal: <a href="{{published_doi}}">{{published_doi}}</a></p>\n<p>Please note that links to your recommendation and reviews published by {{appName}} are available on the <a href="{{published_doi}}">webpage</a> and in the pdf of the published article.</p>\n<p>Thank you again for your contribution.</p>\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>
250	#SubmitterAwaitingSubmissionCOAR	default	{{appName}}: Decision concerning your submission	Mail to submitter to indicate the need to revise their preprint and to make this resubmission via COAR in the preprint server	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p><p>Your article, entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong>, has now been reviewed.</p><p>The referees' comments and the recommender’s decision are shown below. As you can see, the recommender found your article very interesting but suggests certain revisions.</p><p>We shall, in principle, be happy to recommend your article as soon as it has been revised in response to the points raised by the referees.</p><p>When revising your article, we remind you that your article must contain the following sections (see our Guide for Authors in the Help section of the {{appName}} website):</p><p>1) <strong>Data, script and code availability (if applicable)</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Data, statistical scripts, command lines and simulation code must be made available to readers</strong>. They should either be included in the article or deposited <strong>in </strong>an open repository such as Zenodo <strong>with a DOI</strong>. A perennial URL can be provided if no DOI is available; please note that GitHub URL are not perennial.</li><li><strong>If deposited in </strong>an open repository, a reference to <strong>Data, statistical scripts, command lines and simulation code</strong>, with a DOI or a perennial URL, must be provided in the reference list and in the "Data, script and code availability" section</li><li>The "Data, script and code availability" section must clearly indicate&nbsp;<strong>where and how</strong>&nbsp;data can be accessed.</li><li>Wherever possible, data, scripts and code should be provided in machine-readable formats. Avoid PDFs other than for textual supplementary information.</li><li>Metadata should accompany the data, to make the data understandable and reusable by the reader.</li></ul><p>&nbsp;2) <strong>Supplementary information (if applicable)</strong></p><ul><li>Supplementary information (text, tables, figures, videos, etc.) can be referred to in the article. It must be available in an open repository (such as Zenodo, Dryad, OSF, Figshare, Morphobank, Morphosource, Github, MorphoMuseuM, Phenome10k, etc. or any institutional repository, etc...) with a DOI. A perennial URL can be provided if no DOI is available.</li><li>A reference to the supplementary information, with a DOI or a perennial URL, must be provided in the reference list and in the "Supplementary information" section.</li><li>List all documents attached to the manuscript as Supplementary Information in the "Supplementary Information" section.</li></ul><p>3) <strong>Funding (mandatory)</strong></p><ul><li>All sources of funding must be listed in a separate “Funding section”. The absence of funding must be clearly indicated in this section.</li></ul><p>4) <strong>Conflict of interest disclosure (mandatory)</strong></p><ul><li>Authors should declare any potential non-financial conflict of interest (financial conflicts of interest are forbidden, see&nbsp;<a href="https://peercommunityin.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-mce-href="https://peercommunityin.org/">the PCI code of conduct</a>).</li><li>In the absence of competing interests, the authors should add the following sentence to the “Conflict of interest disclosure” section: “The authors declare they have no conflict of interest relating to the content of this article.” If appropriate, this disclosure may be completed by a sentence indicating that some of the authors are PCI recommenders: “XXX is a recommender for PCI XX.”</li></ul><p>5) <strong>Materials and methods (mandatory)</strong></p><ul><li>Details of experimental procedures and quantitative analyses must be made&nbsp;<strong>fully available</strong>&nbsp;to readers, in the text, as appendices, or as Supplementary Information deposited in an open repository, such as Zenodo, Dryad or institutional repositories with a DOI.</li><li>For specimen-based studies,&nbsp;<strong>complete repository information</strong>&nbsp;should be provided and institutional abbreviations should be listed in a dedicated subsection (if applicable). Specimens on which conclusions are based&nbsp;<strong>must be deposited in an accessible and permanent repository</strong>.</li></ul><p>When your revised article is ready, please upload the new version of your manuscript onto the same open archive (or preprint server) in which you deposited the previous version. From this open archive (or preprint server), you could directly resubmit your revised version.&nbsp;<br><br>If you have any questions, please contact us by replying to this email.</p><p>We thank you in advance for submitting your revised version.</p><p>Yours sincerely,</p><p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p><p><br></p><p>{{recommendationProcess}}</p>
251	#UserCompleteSubmissionCOAR	default	{{appName}}: Please complete your submission made from a preprint server	Mail to submitter when submission made from a preprint server	<p>Dear {{destPerson}}</p><p>Thank you for your submission made via a preprint server and sent to {{appName}}.</p><p>We have just created an account for you, so you can proceed with the submission.</p><p>Welcome on board!</p><p>Please click on the following link: <a href="{{linkTarget}}">Complete your submission</a></p><p>and complete your submission as follows:</p><ol><li>Complete all the missing information needed.</li><li>Click on “Save”.</li><li>Your revision has now been resubmitted for consideration by the {{appName}} Managing Board.</li></ol><p>Thanks again for your submission.</p><p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
252	#UserCompleteResubmissionCOAR	default	{{appName}}: Please complete your resubmission made from a preprint server	Mail to submitter when resubmission made from a preprint server via COAR	<p>Dear {{destPerson}}</p><p>Thank you for your resubmission made via a preprint server and sent to {{appName}}.</p><p>Please click on the following link: <a href="{{linkTarget}}" data-mce-href="{{linkTarget}}">Complete your resubmission</a><br data-mce-bogus="1"></p><p>and complete your submission as follows:</p><p>1) Check the title, authors, DOI, abstract, keywords, disciplines, and DOI/URL of data, scripts and code. Do not forget to save your modifications by clicking on the green button.</p><p>2) Click on the blue ‘EDIT YOUR REPLY TO THE RECOMMENDER’ button (mandatory step). You could then write or paste your text, upload your reply as a PDF file, and upload a document with the modifications marked in TrackChange mode. If you are submitting the final formatted version ready to be recommended, you should only add a sentence indicating that you posted the final version on the preprint server. Do not forget to <strong>save your modifications by clicking on the green button</strong>.</p><p>3) Click on the green ‘SEND RESUBMISSION’ button. This will result in your submission being sent to the recommender.</p><p>Once the recommender has read the revised version, they may decide to recommend it directly, in which case the editorial correspondence (reviews, recommender’s decisions, authors’ replies) and a recommendation text will be published by {{appName}} under the license CC-BY.</p><p>Alternatively, other rounds of reviews may be needed before the recommender reaches a favorable conclusion. They may also reject your article, in which case the reviews and decision will be sent to you, but they will not be published or publicly released by {{appName}}. They will be safely stored in our database, to which only the Managing Board has access. You will be notified by e-mail at each stage in the procedure.</p><p>We thank you in advance for submitting your revised version.</p><p>Yours sincerely,</p><p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>
283	#RecommenderDecisionSentBack	default	{{appName}}: You can edit your decision	Mail to recommender when a manager click on the red buton "Send back this decision to the recommender"	<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\n<p>We have changed the status of your decision on the article <span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">by {{articleAuthors}} ({{articleDoi}}). Y</span>ou can now change or edit this decision. Before doing so, you can also invite more reviewers if needed.</p>\n<p><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">T</span><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">o post your new decision on the PCI {{appName}} website, please:</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">1) Go to <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or go to <a href="{{siteUrl}}">{{siteUrl}}</a></span><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">, log in and g</span><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">o to 'FOR RECOMMENDERS'—&gt; 'PREPRINT(S) YOU ARE HANDLING' in the top menu. </span></p>\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">2) Click on the black 'VIEW/EDIT' button at the right end of the corresponding line. </span></p>\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">3) Click on the black 'WRITE OR EDIT YOUR DECISION / RECOMMENDATION’ button. </span></p>\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">4) Indicate your decision by selecting 'I RECOMMEND THIS PREPRINT', 'THIS PREPRINT MERITS REVISION' or 'I REJECT THIS PREPRINT'. </span></p>\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">5) Choose a decision or recommendation title (this is of particular importance only for decisions to recommend the preprint concerned) and write or copy/paste your decision or recommendation text. </span></p>\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">-You can save a draft version of your decision or recommendation text by clicking on the blue 'SAVE' button (you will then have to go through steps 0 to 5 to complete your decision or recommendation).&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">6) To send your decision or recommendation to the managing board for validation, click on the green 'SAVE AND COMPLETE' button. This will result in your decision or recommendation being sent to the managing board for validation.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Thanks in advance.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Best regards</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">The Managing Board of {{appName}} </span><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">{{appName}}</span></p>
\.
